00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','11.79','11.40',NULL,'17/S/16',NULL,'Soil west of W 004, east of 17/S/1.\nStopped excavation due to coming down on a dense layer of stone.','1. layer, possible pit  2. --  3. greyish brown  4. mostly silt, some clay  5. some stones  6. 1m EW x 2.25 NS','E10/E11 baulk',NULL),(305,19,11,'EF10/11 baulk','2017-06-08 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','12.09','11.94',NULL,'W 16/007, 17/S/19',NULL,'Baulk removal to trace top of W 16/007.  Closed when the top of the southern face is articulated.','1. layer  2. loose  3. greyish brown  4. silt with some clay  5. many small stones  6. 1m NS x 4m EW','Baulk between E10, E11, F10, F11',NULL),(306,19,201,'P7','2017-06-05 00:00:00','2017-06-07 00:00:00','17.30','17.02',NULL,'17/S/208',NULL,'Topsoil','1. layer\r\n2. loose sandy soil\r\n3. light brown\r\n4. sandy/silty\r\n5. some large rocks, small rocks, plants\r\n6. 5x5m\r\n7. small area of rocks, continued from P8',NULL,NULL),(307,19,202,'P6','2017-06-05 00:00:00','2017-06-12 00:00:00','17.24','16.89',NULL,'17/S/213',NULL,'Topsoil with lots of pottery and rocks.  Closed once we hit subsoil.','1. Top soil\r\n2. Loose\r\n3. Greyish brown\r\n4. roots, rocks, top soil, silty-sand\r\n5. fieldstones, occasional small-med & large mudbrick, chalk\r\n6. 4mx4m, D 0.13m - 0.24m',NULL,NULL),(308,19,203,'M7','2017-06-05 00:00:00','2017-06-08 00:00:00','16.50','15.65',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Removed top soil to get to subsoil. Went down in 10 cm passes. Square on a slope and slowly trying to level the square. Large boulder in NW corner, still intact, found on the  surface.\nADDITIONAL:  all on a slope','1. layer: top soil\r\n2. loose, rocky\r\n3. grayish-brown\r\n4. silty, sandy,  roots, animal disturbance, shell, very large stones.  \r\n5. small piece of iron knife, snail shell, mudbrick (crude),\n\n handful dump of mudbrick, fragments of oven material\r\n6. 5 x 5m.',NULL,NULL),(309,19,204,'N6','2017-06-05 00:00:00','2017-06-11 00:00:00','16.99','16.43','none','17/S/214 , 17/S/211',NULL,'Topsoil. Rough but easily gone through with a trowel or pick axe.  A large section of this locus is covered by large rocks (mainly in E side). Quite a few giant stones were found, including 2 interesting ones, one on E and one on W.  Excessive pottery found towards the bottom of locus.  We began to find evidence of mudbrick, and the soil became very hard to dig through.','1. Topsoil\r\n2. Loose and clumpy\r\n3. Grayish-brown\r\n4. Sandy - silt\r\n5. Rocks, roots, tsudomorphs, bumped up layer of stones, mudbrick indications, bioturbation, fragments of clam shell.  Increasing no. of ground stones, pumice\r\n6. 4mx4m, D) 0.12 - 0.17 cm',NULL,NULL),(310,19,205,'M6','2017-06-05 00:00:00','2017-06-08 00:00:00','16.49','15.69',NULL,'17/S/209',NULL,'Topsoil\r\nADDITIONAL: For two days wondering whether this could be a wall but it is most probably a collapse of some kind.  Before closing the locus, pretty much the entire area was stones.','1. Layer\r\n2. Loose and crumbly\r\n3. Grey\r\n4. Dry clay\r\n5. Big stones, pottery, roots\r\n6. 5x5',NULL,NULL),(311,19,206,'N7','2017-06-06 00:00:00','2017-06-12 00:00:00','16.18','16.18','+',NULL,NULL,'Locus opened for cleaning and sectioning at the start of the 2017 dig season.  Material collection.\r\nPoint 16.181 rock cluster near center of square.','1. Cleaning locus\r\n2.  Loose soil from the year\r\n3.  Brown-grey\r\n4.  Compact soil & mudbrick; surface\r\n5. Root, animal activity, section collapse\r\n6.  4m x 4m\r\nPoint 16.181 Rock cluster near center of square',NULL,NULL),(312,19,207,'N8','2017-06-07 00:00:00','2017-06-08 00:00:00','15.80','15.63','+',NULL,NULL,'Removal of Eastern half of square that was sectioned higher in 2016 season.  Brought level with Western half of square for visibility and uniformity of square.','1. Layer\r\n2. Compact\r\n3. brown-gray\r\n4. compact silty soil\r\n5. small stones, pottery, flint, bone\r\n6. 2m x 4m, eastern half of square\r\n7. Leveling Eastern half of square to elevation of Western half.',NULL,NULL),(313,19,208,'P7','2017-06-07 00:00:00','2017-06-16 00:00:00','17.19','16.63',NULL,'17/S/222',NULL,'subsoil','1. subsoil\r\n2. crusty on the surface but soft when broken\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n4. some rock, first bits of mudbrick coming through surfact\r\n5. some stone, pebbles, mudbrick, pottery\r\n6. 5 x 5m\r\n7. Mudbrick shows up at relatively similar level.','This square has less stones than the surrounding loci',NULL),(314,19,209,'M6','2017-06-08 00:00:00','2017-06-13 00:00:00','15.69',NULL,'17/S/205','17/S/216, 17/S/217, 17/S/218',NULL,'Subsoil.\nSubsoil removed to discover more stones.  It was decided to treat the possible wall as a wall so the 17/S/216 was opened (SE side of possible wall).  \nSoil crumbly, with a lot of stones and some mudbrick material with small stone inclusions.','1. layer\r\n2. loose and crumbly\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n4. dry clay, some mudbrick material\r\n5. big and small stones, roots\r\n6. 5x5\r\nLocus sheet shows Highest Closing Level is 15.80','Levels are incomplete and inconsistent (opening/closing, AR004)',NULL),(315,19,210,'P8','2017-06-08 00:00:00','2017-06-16 00:00:00','16.90','16.51','+','17/S/231',NULL,'Removed central mound from East baulk toward center of square left from previous season.  Brought to level.','1. Layer\r\n2. Compact\r\n3. dary grey w/ orange\r\n4. silty /  mudbrick\r\n5. stones\r\n6. already on plan\r\nRemoval of central mound from east baulk',NULL,NULL),(316,19,12,'F11/12 baulk','2017-06-11 00:00:00','2017-06-26 00:00:00','11.68','11.45','17/S/8','17/S/22',NULL,'Greyish brown soil, some fist sized rocks.  \nThis locus opened to remove soil from northern face of wall 16/S/3.\nClosed locus due to coming down on dense layer of stones resembling a pavement, and a pile of stones pushed against W 16/003','1. layer  2. somewhat compact  3. greyish brown  4. silt with some clay  5. some fist size stones  6. 130cm EW x 160cm NS','F11/12 baulk',NULL),(317,19,13,'F11/12 baulk','2017-06-11 00:00:00','2017-06-12 00:00:00','12.22','11.90','17/S/8',NULL,NULL,'Greyish brown soil, articulating stones of core of wall 16/S/003','1. core of wall  2. very loose  3. greyish brown  4. silt  5. many small stones (likely formerly part of wall core)  6. 130cm EW x 2m NS','F11 F12 baulk',NULL),(318,19,14,'F11/12 baulk','2017-06-11 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','11.42','11.27','17/S/12',NULL,NULL,'Crusader pit? Opened to investigate apparent cut into layer of stones found beneath 17/S/12.','1. possible pit/cut feature  2. moderately compact  3. brown to reddish brown  4. silt and clay 40/60 - 50/50% respectively  5. --  6. approx. 1m NS with a 50cm radius','F11/12 baulk',NULL),(319,19,211,'N6','2017-06-11 00:00:00','2017-06-13 00:00:00','16.88','16.27','17/S/204','17/S/220',NULL,'Likely to be wall collapse -- sherds angled and overlapping each other.\nRemoved a vast amount of the rocks from the collapse. The dirt was soft in some areas and rough/mudbrick-like in others. Large amount of bone in the NE corner, little elsewhere. After pulling up all the rocks we could, we found fewer large rocks underneath.','1. Wall collapse -- layer\n2. Fairly compact\n3. Grayish-brown\n4. Silty sand to clayish-silt\n5. Rocks (collapse?), roots, chalk, biotubation (tunnels, ants)\n6. Triangle with sides  4.14m x 1.74m x 0.50m    D) 0.26 - 0.48 m\nPhotos REG1, 2-4',NULL,NULL),(320,19,15,'F11/12 baulk','2017-06-12 00:00:00',NULL,'11.80','11.52','17/S/12',NULL,NULL,'Stones abutting northern face of wall 16/S/003\r\nPossible tumble/collapse','1. layer  2. tightly packed  3. --  4. stones','F11/12 baulk',NULL),(321,19,16,'E10/11 baulk','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-15 00:00:00','11.42','11.39','17/S/10','17/S/26',NULL,'Excavating under north end of 17/S/10 to investigate possible pit. Locus closed upon discovery of reddish brown soil at the bottom of this locus.','1. possible pit  2. moderately compact  3. reddish brown  4. fine silt, some clay  5. some small-medium stones','E10/11 baulk',NULL),(322,19,17,'E11','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00','11.60','11.31','17/S/3',NULL,NULL,'Stones which may have belonged to the foundation trench of wall 16/S/004 and/or a pit dating to a later period than wall 16/S/004.  \nOpened to reveal the eastern face of wall 16/S/004','1. possible stone feature  2. moderately compact  3. greyish brown soil  4. stones with some soil, mostly silt, some clay  5. --  6. 1m NW x 1m SE','E11/F11 baulk according to tags',NULL),(323,19,18,'E11','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00','11.19','11.11','17/S/3','17/S/23',NULL,'Tracing pavement 16/S/33.','1. layer  2. --  3. light grey  4. --  5. --  6. ~2.5 NS x 1.5 EW',NULL,NULL),(324,19,19,'E/F10 baulk','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00','12.11','11.83','17S/11','17/S/24',NULL,'Stone layer below topsoil of 17/S/11.','1. layer\r\n2. highly compact stones, loose soil\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n4. mostly silty, little clay\r\n5. \r\n6. 1m NS x 4 m EW','E10/F10 baulk (paperwork says F10/11 but both 17/S/11 and 17/S/24 are E/F10',NULL),(325,19,20,'F12','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00','11.76','11.37','Wall 16/S/003',NULL,NULL,'Possible tumble from core of wall 16/S/003.  Excavated to reveal northern face of wall 16/S/003','1. possible wall collapse; stone tumble\r\n2. moderately compact\r\n3. grey-brown to rich dark brown\r\n4. small-medium stones & silt w/ some clay\r\n5.\r\n6. ~1.2m NS x 2m EW',NULL,NULL),(326,19,21,NULL,'2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'surface finds',NULL,'No Square number',NULL),(327,19,22,'F11/12','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00','11.54','11.54','17/S/12',NULL,NULL,'Layer of stones cut by pits; possible pavement. \r\nFeature, not excavated\r\nNo finds','1. layer, possible pavement',NULL,NULL),(328,19,23,'E11','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00','11.11','10.68','17/S/3, 17/S/16',NULL,NULL,'Prove east of wall 16/S/004\r\nSoil change was almost immediate from grey - reddish brown\r\nVery moist clay then we hit bed rock\r\nSurface did not extend','1. layer\r\n2. friable - clay\r\n3. grey - red/brown\r\n4. soil/clay\r\n5. rocks, small-medium\r\n6. 1.3 WE x .3 N\r\n7. locus closed after reaching bed rock','EC',NULL),(329,19,24,'E/F 10 baulk','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00','11.83','11.59','17/S/19','17/S/38',NULL,'Soil south of wall 16/S/007 and north of stone accumulation in square F10.','1. layer\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n5. some small-medium stones','E10/F10 baulk (tag says E10/E11 baulk)',NULL),(330,19,25,'F12','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-14 00:00:00','11.44','11.13','16/S/20','17/S/41',NULL,'Locus opened as a possible pit excavated in 2016 season as 16/S/20 (?).\nClosed because soil became more compact and clayey & there are some small pebbles & several flat lying sherds.','1. possible pit / layer\r\n2. friable\r\n3. dark greyish brown\r\n4. soil & compact clay\r\n5. pebbles, flay lying pottery, small stones\r\n6. .16 (W) x 1.28 (N)','EC',NULL),(331,19,212,'M7','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-15 00:00:00','16.26','15.86','17/S/203','17/S/225',NULL,'Subsoil layer, covered entire square; very large, spaced out limestone rocks','1. Layer, subsoil\r\n2. loose\r\n3. orange-brown\r\n4. silty-sand\r\n5. very large stones, mudbrick, small shells, worms\r\n6. 4m x 4m,  D) 1-2 cm\r\n7. Locus reduced to corner after rocks removed',NULL,NULL),(332,19,213,'P6','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-15 00:00:00','17.14','16.68','17/S/202','17/S/221, 17/S/226',NULL,'Subsoil. Excavated entire square until appearance of rocks in NW corner at level ~17.01 and soil color change.  That became a new locus (17/S/221); continued on 17/S/213 in the rest of the square','1. subsoil layer\r\n2. sllightly compact\r\n3. greyish-brown\r\n4. silty sandy soil\r\n5. small-large mudbrick, chalk, rocks\r\n6. 4 x 4  D) 22 cm',NULL,NULL),(333,19,214,'N6','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-16 00:00:00','16.88','16.16','17/S/204','17/S/228, 17/S/235',NULL,'Subsoil. \r\nMostly just loose rock and leftover mudbrick.','1. Layer\r\n2. Some sections are loosely compacted, while the mudbrick is very tight\r\n3. Gray\r\n4. Sandy silt\r\n5. Rocks, very stiff soil, occasional inclusions of mudbrick, chalk, bioturbation\r\n6. Triangle with sides 2.70m x 4.14m x 0.0m   D) 0.25 - 0.35 m',NULL,NULL),(334,19,215,'M10','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-13 00:00:00','15.92','15.13','+','17/S/219',NULL,'Topsoil','top soil\r\nloose\r\ngrayish brown\r\nroots, rocks\r\npottery, flint\r\n5 x 5 m',NULL,NULL),(335,19,216,'M6','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-22 00:00:00','16.09','15.53','17/S/209',NULL,NULL,'Opened as an eastern side of a \"wall\"\nOpened to separate material from supposed wall (turned out to be a collapse). Lots of medium stone inclusions until a mudbrick surface was found in the narrowest area and the NE corner (many small pottery sherds). Soon after opening, big pottery sherds among the stone were found.','1. Layer\r\n2. Crumbly\r\n3. Grey, brown\r\n4. Sandy dry clay\r\n5. stones, roots\r\n6. 3.4m NE-SW x 2m WE',NULL,NULL),(336,19,217,'M6','2017-06-13 00:00:00','2017-06-22 00:00:00','15.87','15.40','17/S/209',NULL,NULL,'Working theory is it is a room (upon opening the locus). After days of work we know it is not a room.  Barely a less rocky area among two lines of stones.','1. layer\r\n2. loose\r\n3. brownish grey\r\n4. sandy clay\r\n5. stones, bits of pottery, flint\r\n6. 1.5m x 1.5 m x1.8m NE-SW\r\n7. high density of very small (appr. 1cm x 2cm) pottery sherds','Locus opened when the two lines of stones let us to believe they could have been walls. A lot of stone inclusions and small bits of pottery in loose soil and then mudbrick surface with stone and pottery inclusions.',NULL),(337,19,218,'M6','2017-06-13 00:00:00','2017-06-19 00:00:00','15.96','15.63','17/S/209','17/S/244',NULL,'Layer beneath the subsoil.\r\nMultiple worked stones found, possible slingshots.\r\nPossible exterior to opposite site of larger rocks.','1. Layer\r\n2. Crumbly\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n4. sandy clay\r\n5. stones, roots\r\n6. NS 3.5m x EW 2',NULL,NULL),(338,19,219,'M10','2017-06-13 00:00:00','2017-06-16 00:00:00','15.41','15.06','17/S/215','17/S/232',NULL,'Found wall 21 and 22 within locus\nCorresponds to 17/S/227 in square M11','1. Subsoil\r\n2. Loose\r\n3. Grayish brown\r\n4. Dirt\r\n5. Pottery, bone, flint, small and medium stones, Wall 21\r\n6. 5 x 5',NULL,NULL),(339,19,220,'N6','2017-06-13 00:00:00','2017-06-16 00:00:00','16.70','16.07','17/S/204, 17/S/211','17/S/236',NULL,'Appears to be the bottom layer of wall collapse lying directly under 17/S/211.','1. Layer (under collapse)\r\n2. Loose in most areas, but tightly compacted (mudbrick) in others\r\n3. Brownish-gray\r\n4. Sandy silt\r\n5. chalk, buts of mudbrick\r\n6. 4.14m x 1.74m x 0.50m  D) 0.17m - 0.24m',NULL,NULL),(340,19,26,'E10/11 baulk','2017-06-12 00:00:00','2017-06-13 00:00:00','11.29','11.08','17/S/16',NULL,NULL,'Removal of soil and very small stones below 17/S/16. \nLocus closed upon coming down on a layer of densely packed small-medium stones.','1. layer\r\n2. loose\r\n3. brown\r\n4. friable\r\n5. very small stones\r\n6.','E10/E11 baulk',NULL),(341,19,27,'E11','2017-06-13 00:00:00','2017-06-14 00:00:00','11.73','11.09',NULL,'17/S/32',NULL,'Topsoil\r\nLocus opened to expand square to the east and find surfaces b/w walls 16/3 and 16/4.\r\nClosed after leveling locus','1. layer\r\n2. friable\r\n3. grey-ish brown, reddish when closed\r\n4. clay\r\n5. not many stone inclusions compared to surrounding loci\r\n6. 3.5m (W) x 1.8m (N)',NULL,NULL),(342,19,28,'F10','2017-06-13 00:00:00',NULL,'12.30','12.22','17/S/2','17/S/60',NULL,'Stones and soil; concentrating on the NW corner of the locus to investigate a line of stones extending into square E10 suspected to be a wall. Locus closed after revealing the E face of wall 17/S/1 and reaching a level of more soil than stones.','1. layer\r\n2. tightly packed stones; loose soil\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n4. loose friable\r\n5. very frequent medium-large stones\r\n6. ca 1.5m EW x ca 4 m NS',NULL,NULL),(343,19,29,'F12','2017-06-14 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'17/S/25',NULL,NULL,'Opened due to soil change noticed in 17/S/25.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(344,19,30,'F12/13 baulk','2017-06-14 00:00:00','2017-06-26 00:00:00','12.01','11.27','17/S/9',NULL,NULL,'Peeling layer of rocks to expose face of wall 16/S/003. \r\nStones may have belonged to core of wall and tumbled over wall when face of wall was robbed out.',NULL,'F12/F13 baulk',NULL),(345,19,221,'P6','2017-06-14 00:00:00','2017-06-15 00:00:00','17.01','16.70','17/S/202, 17/S/213','17/S/226',NULL,'Thought to be a wall collapse wo new locus was opened. Upon excavation around the stones proved inconclusive and the stones were taken out. Might be a collapsed wall or rubble heap.','1. Wall collapse\n2. denser soil underneath loose soil\n3. loose soil is reddish brown tint(???) With the compacted soil a greyish brown\n5. small mudbrick, stones\n6. Shape of a right triangle with sides 1.40m (E-W), 1.10m (N-S), 1.90m',NULL,NULL),(346,19,222,'P7','2017-06-14 00:00:00','2017-06-16 00:00:00','17.02','16.49','17/S/208','17/S/240, 17/S/238',NULL,'Subsoil','1. subsoil\n2. crustly on top but soft when picked, compacted\n3. greyish brown\n4. a few large rocks in middle, NW corner more small rocks and compacted\n5. pebbles, rocks, compacted dirt, bits of mudbrick\n6. first two meters of N side\n7. very large sherds of pottery, mudbrick stuck in clumps',NULL,NULL),(347,19,223,'M11','2017-06-14 00:00:00','2017-06-14 00:00:00','15.73','15.16','--','17/S/224',NULL,'Topsoil','1.  topsoil\n2. loose\n3. greyish brown\n4. dirt\n5. pottery, flint, small stones\n6. 2.5 x 5\n7. lots of flint, not a lot of pottery',NULL,NULL),(348,19,224,'M11','2017-06-14 00:00:00','2017-06-23 00:00:00','15.75','15.01','17/S/223','17/S/227',NULL,'Started as subsoil; when we found more rocks, 17/S/227 was created on the W side of the square while 17/S/224 remained on the E side.  Once more rocks were found s of the wall, 17/S/224 remained N of the wall, E side of the square where there were fewer larger rocks','1. Subsoil\r\n2. Loose\r\n3. Grayish brown\r\n4. Silty dirt\r\n5. pottery, bone, flint, small to medium stones\r\n6. 1 x 2 m',NULL,NULL),(349,19,225,'M7','2017-06-15 00:00:00','2017-06-15 00:00:00','15.94','15.61','17/S/203, 17/S/212',NULL,NULL,'New locus opened in case of soil layer change and levelled.','1. layer\r\n2. loose\r\n3.  orange-brown\r\n4. silty-sand\r\n5. large rocks, mud brick, snail shells\r\n6. 4 x 4m',NULL,NULL),(350,19,226,'P6','2017-06-15 00:00:00','2017-06-22 00:00:00','16.93','16.52','17/S/213, 17/S/221','17/S/257',NULL,'Locus opened as suspected to be the inside of a possible wall/building. To the south-east of WL023, may be inside of building.  If so likely to be fill above surface.','1. subsoil\n2. more compact than topsoil\n3. grey-brown, brown\n4. chalk, small-large mudbrick, rocks\n5. some stones (small-large), pottery, mudbrick\n6. 4 x 4   D: N 45cm, S 60cm',NULL,NULL),(351,19,227,'M11','2017-06-15 00:00:00','2017-06-19 00:00:00','15.35','14.99','17/S/224','17/S/242',NULL,'Corresponds to 17/S/219 / 17/S/233 in square M10.\nStarted as a locus above stone surface and WL22.  Once we came down on WL22, the layer moved to south of the wall.','1. layer\r\n2. compact\r\n3. brown\r\n4. silty clay\r\n5. pottery, flint, bone, small to medium field stones\r\n6. 2 x 3 m',NULL,NULL),(352,19,228,'N6','2017-06-15 00:00:00','2017-06-21 00:00:00','16.38','16.07','17/S/214','17/S/254',NULL,'Locus opened as represents cluster of stones surrounding possible standing basalt stone.\nThe ground stone that was found propped up by middle size stones with small stones pushed in to keep it in place. Seems to be intentionally propped.','1. layer (interesting ground stone)\n2. fairly loose\n3. brownish-gray\n4. sandy-silt\n5. chalk, mudbrick, bioturbation\n6. 120cm (NS) x 90 cm (EW),\n\n  D) 47 -',NULL,NULL),(353,19,229,'M7','2017-06-15 00:00:00','2017-06-16 00:00:00','16.75','16.40',NULL,'17/S/233',NULL,'Baulk between M7 and N7, topsoil layer','1. Baulk removed, top soil layer\r\n2. loose\r\n3. gray-brown\r\n4. silty-sand\r\n5. rocks (limestone and basalt),\n\n mudbrick, roots, small shells\r\n6. 1 x 4 m',NULL,NULL),(354,19,230,'M6','2017-06-16 00:00:00','2017-06-19 00:00:00','15.96','15.63','17/S/218',NULL,'17/S/244','SW corner full of stones left and then removed. Left corner higher than 17/S/218. Removed to bring down to level. Concentration of pottery in corner','1. layer\r\n2. large stones\r\n3. grey\r\n4. sandy clay\r\n5. mostly large stones\r\n6. N-SW 140cm x W-S 150 cm\r\n7. corner of stones for removal, more stones underneath',NULL,NULL),(355,19,31,'F12','2017-06-15 00:00:00',NULL,'11.79',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(356,19,32,'E11','2017-06-16 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'17/S/27',NULL,NULL,'-',NULL,NULL,NULL),(357,19,33,'E10','2017-06-16 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00','11.92','11.19','17/S/1',NULL,NULL,'Stone layer below locus 17/S/1 and 17/S/5?\nLocus opened to find the continuation of W 001.\nHoping to articulate the Northern face of W/S/7 and W/S/1 and floating both walls','1. layer\r\n2. loose soil\r\n3.  grayish brown\r\n4. friable\r\n5. mostly rocks\r\n6. 4.8m (W) x 3.6m (S) x 5.2 (NE),\n\n x0.8 (N)\r\n7. large amounts of bone found','EC',NULL),(358,19,34,'F12/13 baulk','2017-06-16 00:00:00','2017-06-19 00:00:00','12.04','11.80','17/S/9',NULL,NULL,'Exposing southern face of wall 16/S./004','1. layer\r\n2. loosely packed\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n4. mainly silty, very little clay\r\n5. many field stones','F12/F13 baulk',NULL),(359,19,35,'D10','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-21 00:00:00','11.56','10.99',NULL,'17/S/65, 17/S/44, 17/S/46',NULL,'Topsoil - Extension of sq E10 2m NS into sq D10 x 3m EW.\r\nOpened to investigate the relationship between walls 16/S/004 and 15/S/003. \r\nLocus closed after removing topsoil, revealing stones east of wall 17/S/001.  \r\nVery few stones west of that wall.','1. layer\r\n2. loose\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n4. friable\r\n5. small-large stones\r\n6. 2m NS x 3m EW',NULL,NULL),(360,19,231,'P8','2017-06-16 00:00:00','2017-06-20 00:00:00','16.59','16.12','17/S/210','17/S/251',NULL,'5 cm passes down at a time. Soil change to a more orange color & more frequent smaller stones brought end of locus. Still looks like a vegetable garden with absence of stones.','1. Layer\n2. Compact\n3. Dark grey\n4. Mudbrick material\n5. very few stones, some pottery (mostly small), flint (some w/ several blades), animal bone, ochre(?)\n6. 3m x 4m,   D: 42cm\n7. Philippe & Martha',NULL,NULL),(361,19,232,'M10','2017-06-16 00:00:00','2017-06-23 00:00:00','15.28','14.92','17/S/219',NULL,NULL,'Corresponds to 17/S/237 in M5.\nDug 17/S/232 down to see if there was a second course to WL 21 & 22. Found a second course on 21, undetermined on 22. There were very few medium or large stones until the very end where some started to come up in the SW corner.','1. layer\r\n2. compact\r\n3. darker brown\r\n4. silty clay\r\n5. pottery, bone, flint, small stones\r\n6. 4 x 4',NULL,NULL),(362,19,233,'M7/N7 baulk','2017-06-16 00:00:00','2017-06-19 00:00:00','16.53','16.16','17/S/229','17/S/243',NULL,'Subsoil in baulk','1. layer, subsoil\n2. loose\n3. orange/grey brown\n4. silty-sand\n5.\n6. 1 x 4m\n7. Put SW of baulk 17/S/234','M7/N7 baulk',NULL),(363,19,234,'M7/N7 baulk','2017-06-16 00:00:00','2017-06-19 00:00:00','16.55','16.08','17/S/229','17/S/243',NULL,'Possible pit identified in baulk during baulk removal; not noticed during excavation of N7 in 2016.','1. possible pit\r\n2. loose\r\n3. brown-grey\r\n4. \r\n5. pottery, mudbrick\r\n6.','M7/N7 baulk',NULL),(364,19,235,'N6','2017-06-16 00:00:00','2017-06-22 00:00:00','16.33','16.02','17/S/214',NULL,NULL,'Area surrounding wall collapse 17/S/236  and standing stone 17/S/228.\nLikely to be same as 17/S/254.','1. Layer (west side)\r\n2. compact (mudbrick)\r\n3. brownish-gray\r\n4. silty-sand\r\n5. mudbrick, chalk, bioturbation\r\n6. 3.73m on one edge; other edges 1.30m - 1.00m - 0.80m',NULL,NULL),(365,19,236,'N6','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-22 00:00:00','16.40','16.06','17/S/220',NULL,NULL,'Mudbrick debris under wall collapse.','1. Layer (mudbrick under walls)\r\n2. compact (mudbrick)\r\n3. brownish-gray\r\n4. silty sand(?)\r\n5. mudbrick, chald, bioturbation\r\n6. triangle with sides 3.73m - 2.75m - 2.39m   D) (96-)',NULL,NULL),(366,19,36,'F10','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-20 00:00:00','12.16','11.91','17/S/6','17/S/64, 17/S/63',NULL,'Removal of rocks obviously not belonging to any feature. Locus closed after removing one layer of stones.','1. layer\r\n2. slightly compact between stones\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n4. \r\n5. small to large stones\r\n6.',NULL,NULL),(367,19,37,'F12/13 baulk','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-20 00:00:00','11.82','NA','17/S/34','17/S/47',NULL,'Opened to reach the lowest level of 2016 season in the south end of F12. Closed upon reaching the level and material of 17/S/39.','1. layer\r\n2. loose\r\n3. brown\r\n4. friable soil\r\n5. some small - medium stones\r\n6. ca. 50cm NS x ca. 90cm EW','F12/F13 baulk',NULL),(368,19,38,'E10/F10 baulk','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-20 00:00:00','11.61','11.61','17/S/24','17/S/40',NULL,'Possible surface. Opened upon finding some flat lying pot sherds at the bottom of 17/S/24. Closed after recovering potsherds and flint from the \"surface.\" 17/S/40 opened to continue excavation in this area.','1. layer\r\n2. highly compact\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n4. dense soil containing a medium-high % of clay\r\n5. very few flat lying pot sherds\r\n6. ca. 2m EW x ca. 70 cm NS (west end) and ca 1m NS (east end)\r\n7. mixed pottery proves this was not a likely surface','E10/F10 baulk',NULL),(369,19,39,'F12','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'17/S/34, 16/S/8?',NULL,NULL,'Exposing Southern face of wall 16/S/003','1. layer',NULL,NULL),(370,19,237,'M11','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-23 00:00:00','15.12','14.89','17/S/227',NULL,NULL,'Corresponds to 17/S/232 in M10.\nSouth of wall 22 where there were ???  on medium or larger stones next to 17/S/242 which had lots of medium stones.','1. layer\r\n2. compact\r\n3. darker brown\r\n4. silty clay\r\n5. pottery, flint, bone, small stones\r\n6. 1 x 2 m',NULL,NULL),(371,19,238,'P7','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','16.73','16.47','17/S/208, 17/S/222',NULL,NULL,'The layer was mostly emply until two small groups of stone appeared, one on the North end near the baulk and one in the Southeast corner. Near the SE stones group, a small group of pot sherds was found which may be restorable.','1. layer\r\n2. compact but loose when picked\r\n3. brownish, sandy-grey\r\n4. silty, sand\r\n5. medium to small rocks, a few stones, pottery\r\n6. 2m x 5m',NULL,'?'),(372,19,239,'P7','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','16.98','16.49','17/S/208, 17/S/222',NULL,NULL,'Locus mostly consists of the rocks on the SW side of the square. As we dug down, more and more worked basalt revealed itself as part of the collection of stones. Some of the basalt was heated and crumbled when picked. The square was left mostly untouched from 20 to 28 June when it was articulated further. Even more worked basalt was revealed, and it is possible that a like of stones may turn out to be part of a wall.','1. layer\r\n2. compact between rocks\r\n3. sandy grey\r\n4. silty between rocks\r\n5. small [???] in soil between rocks\r\n6. roughly 1 x 2.5m',NULL,NULL),(373,19,240,'P7','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','16.70','16.40','17/S/222',NULL,NULL,'This layer is roughly 5cm + until coming down on burth-reddish mudbrick. Before that it had a layer of pebbles.','1. layer\r\n2. crusty subsoil, dusty when picked\r\n3. brownish gray\r\n4. dusty, crusty\r\n5. small, medium rocks.  Pottery, some bones, bits of mudbrick\r\n6. roughly 1m x 1.5m\r\n7. some upright pottery',NULL,NULL),(374,19,241,'P6','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','16.72','16.48','17/S/221, 17/S/226',NULL,NULL,'Layer of rocks to the NW of wall 23. May represent tumble off of the wall.','1. Layer\r\n2. loose\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n4. sandy silt\r\n5. some mudbrick, layer of medium rocks\r\n6. triangle w sides 250cm - 180cm - 310 cm',NULL,NULL),(375,19,242,'M11','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-23 00:00:00','15.11','14.99','17/S/227',NULL,NULL,'We noticed that there were large rocks coming up south of WL22 and that there were no rocks west of it so the area south of the wall was split into 17/S/242 and 17/S/237. 17/S/242 was the layer of dirt and smaller stones removed above the layer of rocks.','1. layer\r\n2. compact\r\n3. darker brown\r\n4. silty clay\r\n5. pottery, small to medium stones\r\n6. 1.5 x 2m',NULL,NULL),(376,19,243,'M7/N7 baulk','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-20 00:00:00','16.31','15.93','17/S/233',NULL,NULL,'Last part of baulk removed between M7 and N7. Made it down to mudbrick seen in sections of N7.  Likely to be just above secondary surface relating to large ground stone.','1. layer\r\n2. more compact\r\n3. light brown\r\n4. silty soil\r\n5. \r\n6. 1m x 4m','M7/N7 baulk',NULL),(377,19,244,'M6','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-22 00:00:00','15.76','15.58','17/S/230, 17/S/218',NULL,NULL,'After getting the corner (17/S/230) to the level of 17/S/218, both loci were closed and merged to form this layer, 17/S/244.','1. Layer\r\n2. Loose\r\n3. brownish grey\r\n4. sandy clay\r\n5. big stones\r\n6. 4m (N-S) x 2m (W-E) x',NULL,NULL),(378,19,245,'M10/N10 baulk','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-19 00:00:00','15.91','15.70',NULL,'17/S/246',NULL,'Topsoil. Corresponds to 17/S/215 in M10.','1. Top soil\r\n2. loose\r\n3. grayish brown\r\n4.  silty soil\r\n5. hay, pottery, roots, small stones, flint\r\n6. 1 x 4m','M10/N10 baulk',NULL),(379,19,246,'M10/N10 baulk','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-19 00:00:00','15.87','15.62','17/S/245','17/S/247',NULL,'Subsoil. Corresponds to 17/S/219 in M10.','1.  sub soil\r\n2.  loose\r\n3.  grayish brown\r\n4.  silty soil\r\n5.  few small to medium stones, pottery, flint\r\n6. 1 x 4m','M10/N10 baulk',NULL),(380,19,247,'M10/N10 baulk','2017-06-19 00:00:00','2017-06-20 00:00:00','15.73','15.29','17/S/246','17/S/248, 17/S/249, 17/S/250',NULL,'Layer before we came down on wall and mudbrick on wall. Once we saw the mud brick we changed to three loci: one on the wall, one SW of the wall, and one NE of the wall.','1. layer\n2. compact\n3. brown\n4. silty clay\n5. pottery, small stones, flint, bone, mudbrick\n6. 1 x 4','M10/N10 baulk',NULL),(381,19,40,'E10/F10 baulk','2017-06-19 00:00:00',NULL,'11.61',NULL,'17/S/38',NULL,NULL,'-','1. layer','E10/F10 baulk',NULL),(382,19,41,'F12/F13 baulk','2017-06-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5. some (very occasional) tuff\r\n6. 190cm EW x',NULL,'F12/F13 baulk',NULL),(383,19,42,'E10/F10 baulk','2017-06-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'17/S/11','17/S/52','17/S/7','-',NULL,'E10/F10 baulk',NULL),(384,19,43,'E11','2017-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'17/S/32',NULL,NULL,'Opened to find extent of pavement 16/S/33.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(385,19,44,'D10','2017-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,'11.46','11.23','17/S/35',NULL,NULL,'Loose/floating rocks abutting North part of wall 17/S/001\r\n4 rodent holes in baulk\r\nThis locus was opened to find the extent of wall 17/S/001','1. layer\r\n2. loose soil, chunks of compacted soil\r\n3. grayish-brown\r\n4. friable\r\n5. loose rocks, 2 large rocks of wall\r\n6. 1.34 x 1.03 m\r\n7. mudbrick found in South East corner of locus',NULL,NULL),(386,19,45,'E10','2017-06-21 00:00:00','2017-06-23 00:00:00','11.83','11.42','17/S/5',NULL,NULL,'Stone layer.  Locus opened to find continuation of wall 17/S/001\r\nIt indeed continues from the large stones uncovered in F10. This excavated only in a narrow trench across the square but we will continue to remove stones','1. layer\r\n2. loose - med-loose\r\n3. grayish brown\r\n4. friable\r\n5. rocks, small-med','EC',NULL),(387,19,248,'M10/N10 baulk','2017-06-20 00:00:00','2017-06-23 00:00:00','15.43','15.06','17/S/247',NULL,NULL,'Southwest of WL24 in baulk M10/N10 discovered two more rocks that were part of wall 24 became visible while digging down. The mudbrick from N10 went all the way to the wall and also could be seen under wall 24.','1. Layer\n2. Compact\n3. Brown\n4. Silty clay\n5. pottery, flint, bone, small and medium size stones, mudbrick\n6. small triangle','M10/N10 baulk',NULL),(388,19,249,'M10/N10 baulk','2017-06-20 00:00:00','2017-06-23 00:00:00','15.35','15.18','17/S/247',NULL,NULL,'Above WL24 in baulk M10/N10. Started as a rectangle across the baulk following where WL24 was believed to go. It became clear that the wall stopped short, rocks possibly missing from the N face. There was discovered mudbrick material sitting on the wall.','1.  Layaer\r\n2.  compact\r\n3.  brown\r\n4.  silty clay\r\n5.  pottery, bone flint, small stones, mud brick\r\n6. 0.5 x 1.5 m','M10/N10 baulk',NULL),(389,19,250,'M10/N10 baulk','2017-06-20 00:00:00','2017-06-23 00:00:00','15.34','15.08','17/S/247',NULL,NULL,'Northeast of WL24 in baulk M10/N10. Came down on lots of mudbrick type material, runs along wall 24 and connects to mud brick material from 17/S/267.','1. layer\r\n2. compact\r\n3. brown\r\n4. silty clay\r\n5. possible taboon (oven) material, pottery, flint, bone, small rocks, few medium rocks, mudbrick\r\n6. 1 x 3m [???]','M10/N10 baulk',NULL),(390,19,251,'P8','2017-06-21 00:00:00','2017-06-22 00:00:00','16.17','15.97','17/S/231','17/S/259, 17/S/260',NULL,'5cm - 10cm passes were used to take the layer down around a few small stones in the square. New loci opened: 17/S/259 for rocky outcropping in SW corner of square (possible pit) and 17/S/260 in the main part of the square at levels even with or lower than the possible pit.','1. layer\n2. more compace / mudbrick material\n3. orange w/ grey\n4. mudbrick material\n5. rocks (very few), flint (several blades), animal bone, pottery, worked stone\n6. 3m x 4m   D: 15 cm\n7. Philippe and Martha',NULL,NULL),(391,19,252,'M7/N7 baulk','2017-06-20 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','16.09','15.77','17/S/243','17/S/278, 17/S/282',NULL,'This locus stretches from M7 into square N7 and ends at the baulk of N7/P7. We lowered this locus down to the level already excavated around the grindstone. Appears to be directly on top of EB surface.','1. layer\r\n2. mudbrick - slightly compacted surface-like\r\n3. gray-brown\r\n4. silty\r\n5. bit and small rocks, pebbles, pottery, flint, bone, snail shells, animal holes, mudbrick\r\n6. 3.52m x 3.6m /1.75m x 0.15-0.16 m','M7/N7 baulk and square N7',NULL),(392,19,253,'N7/P7 baulk','2017-06-21 00:00:00','2017-06-21 00:00:00','17.18','16.98',NULL,NULL,NULL,'This locus was mostly baulk removal consisting of loose topsoil and subsoil.','1. baulk\n2. loose\n3. darker soil\n4. silty soil\n5. loose stones, small pebbles, pottery\n6. 1 x 5 m','N7/P7 baulk',NULL),(393,19,254,'N6','2017-06-21 00:00:00','2017-06-22 00:00:00','16.22','15.99','17/S/228',NULL,NULL,'Area under suspected standing stone cluster 17/S/228. Likely to be the same as 17/S/235.','1. Layer\r\n2. Fairly loose\r\n3. Gray-brown\r\n4. Sandy-silt\r\n5. chalk\r\n6. 208, 105, 217   D) 13cm',NULL,NULL),(394,19,255,'N7/P7 baulk','2017-06-21 00:00:00','2017-06-22 00:00:00','17.10','16.75','17/S/253','17/S/256',NULL,'Baulk. Mostly subsoil, very easy to pick and remove.','1. Baulk\r\n2. loose\r\n3. darker soil\r\n4. loose, easy to pick\r\n5. rocks, both small and large\r\n6. 1 x 5m','N7/P7 baulk',NULL),(395,19,46,'D10','2017-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,'11.43','10.99','17/S/35',NULL,NULL,'Locus was opened to find the extent of wall.\nMany loosely compacted rocks found in locus.','1. layer\r\n2. loose\r\n3. dark brown\r\n4. friable\r\n5. rocks, med-larger\r\n6. 1.95 x 1.07','Note that levels are inconsistent -- PT1 higher than opening',NULL),(396,19,47,'F12/F13 baulk','2017-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Opened due to soil change in 17/S/39.','1. layer\r\n2. hightlycompact\r\n3.\r\n4.\r\n5. frequent 