e\r\n3. grayish-brown\r\n4. sandy, silt\r\n5. roots\r\n6. 1 x 1m approx','Baulk at intersection of N6/N7/P6/P7',NULL),(413,19,264,'N6/N7 baulk','2017-06-22 00:00:00','2017-06-23 00:00:00','16.96','16.08','17/S/262','17/S/268',NULL,'Removal of fill in baulk. Two buckets full of groundstone removed in fill as well as a large quantity of pottery.','1.  Fill\r\n2.  loose\r\n3.  brownish-grey\r\n4.  sandy - silt\r\n5.  Roots, v. freq. small and med limestone field stones, freq. fragments of worked stone (limestone and basalt)\r\n6. 3m x 1m approx.','N6/N7 baulk',NULL),(414,19,54,'F9/F10 baulk','2017-06-22 00:00:00',NULL,'12.41',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'-',NULL,'F9/F10 baulk',NULL),(415,10,85,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(416,19,265,'N7/P7 baulk','2017-06-22 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','16.72','16.36','17/S/256',NULL,NULL,'Baulk. The baulk was removed because it sits right above the burnt mudbrick which can be seen from N7. Excavation was halted about 5cm above the mudbrick as a buffer to protect it from weather.','1. baulk\r\n2. compact\r\n3. greyish tan\r\n4. silty clay\r\n5. pottery, flint, pebbles to med-size stones\r\n6. 1 x 5m','N7/P7 baulk',NULL),(417,19,266,'N6/N7/P6/P7  baulk','2017-06-23 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','16.65','16.39','17/S/263',NULL,NULL,'Layer similar to 17/S/275 when brought down. Same mudbrick material.','1. layer (subsoil) (below pit)\r\n2. more compact than pit soil\r\n3. greyish brown w/ some orange\r\n4. mudbrick material\r\n5. pottery, flint, some small stones, bone\r\n6. 1m x 1m approx.','N6/N7/P6/P7 baulk',NULL),(418,19,55,'E10/F10 baulk','2017-06-22 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'17/S/24',NULL,NULL,'Possible stone installation against surface of wall 16/S/007',NULL,'E10/F10 baulk',NULL),(419,19,56,'E/F 9/10 baulk','2017-06-22 00:00:00',NULL,'11.69',NULL,'17/S/7',NULL,NULL,'Opened due to discovery of mudbrick below the level of wall 17/S/001',NULL,'baulk dividing E9 E10 F9 F10',NULL),(420,19,57,'F9/F10 baulk','2017-06-23 00:00:00',NULL,'12.10',NULL,'17/S/56','17/S/61',NULL,'Stone layer S of locus 17/S/56\nMany sherds of possible Mamluk jar w/ locus below it',NULL,'F9/F10 baulk',NULL),(421,19,58,'F11','2017-06-23 00:00:00',NULL,'11.30','11.23',NULL,NULL,NULL,'-','6. 110 EW x 80 NS',NULL,NULL),(422,19,59,'E9/E10 baulk','2017-06-25 00:00:00','2017-06-27 00:00:00','11.55','11.31','17/S/45','17/S/68',NULL,'Articulating the Western face of wall 17/S/001','1. layer\r\n2. friable\r\n3. grayish brown\r\n4. friable\r\n5. rocks, pottery, flint, bone, small stones med-large stones\r\n6, 2m x 1m','E9/E10 baulk   EC VESSEL: PT002, VS001 votive jarlet June 26.  Logged in as Artifact AR99',NULL),(423,19,60,'F10','2017-06-25 00:00:00','2017-06-26 00:00:00','11.77','11.55','17/S/28','17/S/64',NULL,'Removal of soil to expose Eastern face of wall 17/S/001','1.\r\n2. loose\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n4.\r\n5. some small fieldstones',NULL,NULL),(424,19,267,'M10/N10 baulk','2017-06-23 00:00:00','2017-06-23 00:00:00','15.30','15.04','17/S/249',NULL,NULL,'Located NW of the end of W24, where W24 might have extended to but does not. Came down on the same layer of mud brick from N10 that goes to the other side of the wall. Connects the mud brick from N10, 17/S/248 and 17/S/250.','1. layer\r\n2. compact\r\n3. brown\r\n4. silty clay\r\n5. pottery, mud brick, small and medium stones\r\n6. small area at end of wall 24','M10/N10 baulk',NULL),(425,19,268,'N6/N7 baulk','2017-06-23 00:00:00','2017-06-26 00:00:00','16.22','15.98','17/S/264',NULL,NULL,'Layer above cluster of stones at bottom of the baulk.','1. layer\r\n2. slightly compact around stones\r\n3. brownish gray\r\n4. more sandy with some mudbrick material\r\n5. many small - medium stones\r\n6. 3m x 1m approx','N6/N7 baulk',NULL),(426,19,269,'N10','2017-06-23 00:00:00','2017-06-27 00:00:00','15.57','14.97',NULL,'17/S/272, 17/S/277, 17/S/281, 17/S/284',NULL,'Cleaning prior to reworking of square','1. cleaning\r\n2. loose\r\n3. greyish brown\r\n4. silty