,280,'N6/P6 baulk','2017-06-26 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','16.60','16.47','17/S/276',NULL,NULL,'Layer in baulk beneath subsoil. Might potentially connect with rocks in P6\nWe found a good deal of small groundstones and worked stones just barely to the West of the large groundstone in the East side of the baulk.','1. layer\r\n2. slightly compact\r\n3. grayish-brown\r\n4. sandy-silty\r\n5. bioturbation, mudbrick (burnt)\r\n6. 1 x 4m','N6/P6 baulk',NULL),(438,19,61,'F9/F10 baulk','2017-06-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'17/S/57',NULL,NULL,'-',NULL,'F9/F10 baulk',NULL),(439,19,62,'F10','2017-06-26 00:00:00',NULL,'12.38','11.55','17/S/6?',NULL,NULL,'Stones',NULL,NULL,NULL),(440,19,63,'F10','2017-06-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(441,19,64,'F10','2017-06-26 00:00:00',NULL,'11.71',NULL,'17/S/60, 17/S/62, 17/S/63',NULL,NULL,'-',NULL,NULL,NULL),(442,19,65,'D10','2017-06-27 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'17/S/35',NULL,NULL,'Checking possibility of Byzantine building extension',NULL,NULL,NULL),(443,19,66,'F10','2017-06-28 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'17/S/64',NULL,NULL,'Finding base of wall 16/S/004, 16/S/007, and 17/S/001',NULL,NULL,NULL),(444,19,67,'F10','2017-06-27 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00',NULL,'11.49','17/S/28',NULL,NULL,'Densely packed stones east of wall 17/S/001','1. layer\r\n2. tightly packed\r\n3. NA\r\n4. small to medium size stones\r\n5. some burnt mudbrick chunks\r\n6. ~2.2m EW x ~1.3m NS',NULL,NULL),(445,19,68,'E9/E10 baulk','2017-06-27 00:00:00',NULL,'11.50',NULL,'17/S/59','17/S/70',NULL,'Continue to level, tracing some more patches of possible pavement 17/S/71.  Some medium stones appear, several of which seem to be arranged in what seems to be a segment of an E-W wall \n17/S/70 pottery found flat lying on 17/S/71.','1. layer\r\n2. loose\r\n3. grayish light brown\r\n4. silty soil\r\n5. possible surfact\r\n6. 4m WE x 1m NS\r\n7. One chunk of mud brick','E9/E10 baulk',NULL),(446,19,69,'D10/E10 baulk','2017-06-27 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00','11.52','11.29','17/S/1',NULL,NULL,'Checking possible wall branching west from wall 16/S/004.  Excavating here to determine whether there may be an E-W wall here abutting / bonding w/ W 17/001.  Some large [stones?]','1. layer\r\n2. loose soil / rocks\r\n3. grayish brown soil\r\n4. friable\r\n5. some small rocks','D10/E10 baulk',NULL),(447,19,70,'E9/E10 baulk','2017-06-27 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00','11.43','12.43','17/S/59, 17/S/68',NULL,NULL,'Sitting directly on top of surface pavement of 17/S/71','1. surface\r\n2. loose soil on top of surface\r\n3. light grey\r\n4. silty soil\r\n5. \r\n6. .03m x .02m','E9/E10 baulk  NB: Elevations are inconsistent',NULL),(448,19,281,'N10','2017-06-26 00:00:00','2017-06-27 00:00:00','15.52','15.05','17/S/269, 17/S/277, 17/S/272','17/S/284',NULL,'Mudbrick layer on East side of the square taken down to level square with a second lower level in the Northwest corner. May have some restoration pottery in this locus since it was only just below 17/S/272.','1. layer\r\n2. compact\r\n3. light brown\r\n4. mudbrick material\r\n5. pottery, bone, flint, small stones\r\n6. 2 x 3.5m',NULL,NULL),(449,19,282,'N7','2017-06-27 00:00:00','2017-06-27 00:00:00','16.11','15.89','17/S/252, 17/S/243',NULL,NULL,'A semi-circle of stones in the E wall of N7. Possible pit w/compact dirt at the bottom. Some rocks fell in.','1. possible pit in E wall of N7\r\n2. loose\r\n3. gray-brown\r\n4. silty soil\r\n5. big rock, pottery, flint, bone; mudbrick w/ pottery, flint, bone inside\r\n6. 57cm x 130cm x D: 0.12m - 0.5m',NULL,NULL),(450,19,283,'N6/N7 baulk','2017-06-27 00:00:00','2017-06-27 00:00:00','16.65','16.36','17/S/266',NULL,NULL,'Final removal of the [???] of the baulk between N6/N7. Appears to be fill and is adjacent to possible installation. Likely to be just inside truncation for robber cut.','1. layer\r\n2. slightly compact\r\n3. grayish-brown\r\n4. sandy silt\r\n5. mudbrick, bioturbation\r\n6. 1 x 1m','N6/N7 baulk',NULL),(451,19,284,'N10','2017-06-27 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','15.20','14.95','17/S/269, 17/S/281',NULL,NULL,'Mudbrick layer started as North and East sides of square leveled down to South West corner to include whole square south of Wall 24. Entire layer mud brick with few rocks on east side.','1. layer\r\n2. compact\r\n3. light browh\r\n4. mud brick material\r\n5. pottery, flint, bone\r\n6. 4 x 4m',NULL,NULL),(452,19,285,'N6/N7 baulk','2017-06-27 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','16.21','16.11','17/S/268',NULL,NULL,'Layer of rocks at base of baulk and robber cut. Possibly seals EB layer.','1. layer (area of rocks under mudbrick)\r\n2. fairly compact\r\n3. grayish brown\r\n4. sandy - silt\r\n5. rocks\r\n6. 3 x 1m',NULL,NULL),(453,19,71,'E9/E10 baulk','2017-06-27 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00','11.43',NULL,'17/S/70',NULL,NULL,'pavement','1. surface\r\n2. stones & pottery\r\n3. light grey\r\n4. compact small rocks\r\n5. small pottery and small rocks\r\n7. locus is the pavement and pottery included in the surface','no pottery',NULL),(454,19,72,'F9/F10 baulk','2017-06-28 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','11.83','11.59','17/S/69','17/S/61',NULL,'Opened to remove fist sized stones, esp on northern edge to try and reach elevation(?) west of W 17/001','1. layer\r\n2. loose soil w/ some mudbrick\r\n3. grayish dark brown\r\n4. med-large rocks, friable soil\r\n5. rocks, large stones, pottery, bone\r\n6. 2m x 2m','F9/F10 baulk',NULL),(455,19,286,'P6','2017-06-28 00:00:00','2017-06-29 00:00:00','16.66','16.46','17/S/241, 17/S/257',NULL,NULL,'Cleaning locus from end of season.','1. cleaning/sectioning\r\n2. loose - dense\r\n3. greyish-brown\r\n4. silty, mudbrick\r\n5. rocks\r\n6. 4m x 4m',NULL,NULL),(456,19,287,'M7/N7 baulk','2017-06-28 00:00:00','2017-06-28 00:00:00','16.11','15.61','17/S/252, 17/S/278, 17/S/282',NULL,NULL,'Cleaning square at end of season.','1. cleaning and sectioning\r\n2. mudbrick, slightly compact\r\n3. gray / grayish-brown\r\n4. silty\r\n5. small shells, mudbrick, animal holes, big rocks, small rocks\r\n6.','M7/N7 baulk',NULL),(457,16,1,'Trench 1','2016-05-30 00:00:00','2016-05-31 00:00:00','73.62','72.72','x','16/L/2',NULL,'Topsoil.  Opened trench to search for road from 1900s-era photographs (40s?) that makes a 90-degree turn.','Trench 1.2m x 6.5m N-S x 32 cm deep. Topsoil.  Loose greyish-brown soil. Many gravel-size and fist-size stones. Flint -- most unworked.  A small amount of body sherds -- mostly worn and unindicative.  Some modern metal is found in this locus, but also a horse-shoe nail in its north.',NULL,NULL),(458,16,2,'Trench 1','2016-05-31 00:00:00','2016-06-01 00:00:00','73.3','72.54','16/L/1','16/L/3',NULL,'Very little pottery & flint, just below topsoil.  Small piece of glass and small metal artifact [later CANCELLED] found in the middle of the trench, not much order or context.  Some flint, mostly unworked.  Since we weren\'t finding much, we decided to only dig a small portion of the trench (turned into 16/L/3).','Trench 1.2m x 6.5m.  Brown soil. Loose.  Slightly more compact than the topsoil locus above it (16/L/1), but probably due to the fact that there are less plant roots here.  Inclusions include small stones and a very small amount of flint and pottery.',NULL,NULL),(459,16,3,'Trench 1','2016-06-01 00:00:00','2016-06-02 00:00:00','72.64',NULL,'16/L/2','16/L/4',NULL,'1.2 x 2 m. trench opened below trench of locus 16/L/2, 58 cm deep.  High amount of rocks with no order.  Opened the trench in the larger 1.2 x 6m. trench because we found nothing.  There was Bronze or Iron Age pottery in higher amounts, 1 shell, and some apparent seeds (no flint) with possible mudbrick at the bottom of the layer, but unsure of what anything may be.','1. layer, 1.2 x 2m trench in north of large trench.  2. compact  3. dark brown  4.  sandy-silty  5. fist-sized/medium sized rocks, high/moderate amount possible mudbrick at bottom of locus  6. 1.2 x 2m N-S x48cm deep trench in northern part of large trench. 7. Larger amount of what appears to be Bronze Age pottery.',NULL,NULL),(460,16,4,'Trench 1','2016-06-02 00:00:00','2016-06-02 00:00:00','72.16',NULL,'16/L/3','none',NULL,'Small section at north of trench. Opened because were digging through what we thought may be a possible brick or mudbrick, but turned out to just be bedrock.  No pottery.','1. layer 2. very compact 3. chalky & grey  4. deteriorated rock  5. rocks (crumbled)  6. N-S) 0.5m x E-W 1.2m x D) 6cm, north of trench 7. deteriorated bedrock.',NULL,NULL),(461,17,1,'Feature 1','2016-05-29 00:00:00','2016-05-29 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cleared rock cut feature southwest of shaft (~14.5 m from shaft). Wash included large number of tesserae and flint pieces (cores, small blades, debitage). An arrowhead and piece of glass were found to the northwest of carved feature. Perforation in SW.','1. Carved bedrock layer  \n2. loose  \n3. Dark brown  \n4. Wash, topsoil -- silty clay \n5. Flint, tesserae, few small fieldstones  \n6. 0.9m x 1.4m; 20 cm. deep  \n7. Sloped -- hill wash',NULL,NULL),(462,17,2,'Feature 2','2016-05-30 00:00:00','2016-05-31 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Continued to expose bedrock, working toward shaft. Excavation yielded flint and tesserae, both of which decreased as work progressed. The bedrock exhibits evidence of quarrying close to the opening of the bedrock.','1. layer  \n2. Loose soil  \n3. Greyish brown  \n4. Silty clay  \n5. Many small and a few medium fieldstones  \n6. NW-SE 4.7m x NW-SW 3.0 m Greatest depth ~.75m',NULL,NULL),(463,17,3,'Feature 3','2016-05-31 00:00:00','2016-06-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Began exposing bedrock around opening in bedrock. East of \"dromos\" indicates quarrying, removing a piece 1.5m x 0.8m. On west side, exposed piece 2.3m x 1.0m of flat bedrock (finished surface), with some flat stones covered with tumble.','1. layer  \n2. Loose soil  \n3. Greyish brown  \n4. Silty clay  \n5. Small, medium and large fieldstones  \n6. NW-SE 4.5m x NW-SW 3.5 m',NULL,NULL),(464,17,4,'Feature 3','2016-06-02 00:00:00','2016-06-06 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Began clearing wash from rectangular opening in bedrock 2.80 x .80 m with two steps going down. Initially referred to as a possible \"dromos.\" Excavation yielded pottery, a few pieces of flint, a few metal artifacts, and a piece of basalt. Worked until level with ceiling of underground chamber.','1. layer  \n2. Loose soil  \n3. Greyish brown  \n4. Silty clay  \n5. Medium fieldstones  \n6. 2.8m x 0.8 m; greatest depth 0.7m',NULL,NULL),(465,17,5,'Feature 4','2016-06-03 00:00:00','2016-06-05 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cleared wash (likely from Feature 003) that had been deposited along NE side of chamber. Excavation yielded a large number of animal bones under two large pieces of sheet metal.','1. layer  \n2. Loose soil  \n3. Greyish brown  \n4. Silty clay  \n5. Small and medium fieldstones  \n6.  0 - 0.5m',NULL,NULL),(466,17,6,'Feature 4','2016-06-05 00:00:00','2016-06-05 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'16/Q/5',NULL,NULL,'Cleared next layer beneath \"wash\" (16/Q/5). Included large number of bird and rodent bones, and a few from large mammals (teeth & vertebrae). Some fragments of green modern glass were also found. Closed locus upon reaching bottom of cavity in this area.','1. layer  \n2.  Loose soil  \n3. Dark brown  \n4. Humus  \n5. Small and medium fieldstones  \n6. N-S 2.6m x E-W 1.6m x max depth 1.0m',NULL,NULL),(467,17,7,'Feature 5','2016-06-06 00:00:00','2016-06-07 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Exposed bedrock surface in attempt to trace possible architecture, suggested by presence of large stones at edge of cleared area next to the shaft opening. Excavation yielded a few pieces of glass, tesserae, flint, and pottery.','1. layer  \n2. Loose soil  \n3. Greyish brown \n4. Silty clay  \n5.  Small & medium fieldstones',NULL,NULL),(468,17,8,'Feature 5','2016-06-07 00:00:00','2016-06-07 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Continuing to expose bedrock located north of the shaft (Feature 004). Removal of soil revealed more quarrying cut marks in this area.  Pottery, flint, and tesserae were collected.','1. layer  \n2.  Loose soil  \n3. Greyish brown  \n4. Silty clay  \n5.  Small fieldstones',NULL,NULL),(469,17,9,'Feature 6','2016-06-09 00:00:00','2016-06-16 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Removing soil and exposing bedrock around installation (identified as an olive crusher).  Initial stages of excavation yielded a few metal artifacts and very few pottery sherds.  The number of sherds increased as work progressed.  In addition, we encountered more compact, yellow-red soil, which often included small fieldstones. In the course of excavation we traced a curved line of stone south of the installation, perhaps delineating the workspace, and exposed cuts in the bedrock.','1. layer  \n2. Varied -- initially very loose, with some areas having tightly compacted soil  \n3. Yellowish red  \n4. Silty clay  \n5. Roots, small and medium fieldstones',NULL,NULL),(470,18,1,'F11','2016-05-29 00:00:00','2016-05-30 00:00:00','12.062','11.808','x','16/S/2, 16/S/3, W 003',NULL,'This area is the eastern most part of a 5x5 square created to trace the walls coming from 2015 (square ???) from the east. There was a small amount of pottery, flint, and a couple of bones as well as 3 pieces of worked basalt.','1. layer  2. loose  3. dark gray brown  4. silty  5. pebbles and field stones  6. n-s 5m x e-w 2m x 25cm deep  7. topsoil','This locus is on a slope. Three pottery buckets, all mixed and minus. Some Rom/Byz, gana, wadi rabbah. Worked basalt.',NULL),(471,18,2,'F11','2016-05-31 00:00:00','2016-05-31 00:00:00','11.802','11.624','16/S/1',NULL,NULL,'Excavation north of 16/WL001. Possible surface filled in with field stones and dirt. Consider the possibility that this is a surface on which 16/WL003 is sitting. Among the debris we found pieces of flint.','1. layer  2. compact  3. brown  4. silty clay  5. field stones  6. 2.24m EW x 1.72 NS x 22 cm deep  7. Possible surface next to wall 003',NULL,NULL),(472,18,3,'F11','2016-05-31 00:00:00','2016-06-02 00:00:00','12.152','12.018','16/S/1',NULL,NULL,'Section south east of 5x5 square. Excavating to find southern wall edge of 16/WL003 under 16/S/1.','1. layer  2. compact  3. brown  4. clay  5. field stones  6. 1.84m EW x 1.54m NS x 14 cm deep  7. Southern surface next to 16/WL003','Not as many rocks as in 16/S/2 and 16/S/5 on north side wall. The locus had pottery, small nail, worked basalt and flint. We hoped to find the southern face of 16/WL001 and found part of it but robbed out.',NULL),(473,18,4,'F11','2016-06-01 00:00:00','2016-06-01 00:00:00','12.056',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Pit discovered 2015. Excavating fill. Turns out this was excavated in 2015. See report from last year.','1. pit  2. loose  3. gray  4. silty  5. none  6. 7 cm deep  7. fill',NULL,NULL),(474,18,5,'F11','2016-06-01 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','11.552','11.29','16/S/1, 16/S/2',NULL,NULL,'In NE corner of the 5x5 square in northern face of Wall 003. We came down to a surface with pottery, bones, on a surface that was composed of field stones and compacted dirt (16/S/8 was an expansion of this). Equated with 16/S/28, 16/S/29, and possibly 16/S/30.','1. layer  2. loose  3. brown/gray  4. silty clay  5. field stones  6. 2.24m EW x 1.72m NS x 17 cm deep',NULL,NULL),(475,18,6,'E11','2016-06-02 00:00:00','2016-06-14 00:00:00','11.903','11.35','x','16/S/21',NULL,'2.5 x 2.5 m. square, N of square. Topsoil. Trying to see where surrounding walls on F11 North and D11 South of this square are going. Seems not to be in any order. The method focused on digging between the rocks. It\'s unclear, but the walls may not continue in this area. Expanded N 1.6 m. Making the dimensions of the square 2.5 m. E-W x 4.1 m. N-S. Square continues to D11 and F11 switched locus as started removing stones, but soil remained the same.','1. layer  2. loose  3. gray-brown  4. sandy-silty  5. small to large fieldstones, pebbles  6. 4.1m N-S x 2.5 EW x 13 cm deep  7. topsoil clearing',NULL,NULL),(476,18,7,'F12','2016-06-05 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','12.24','11.6','x','16/S/9, 16/S/10',NULL,'Topsoil. Square opened to try and find wall between squares on east and west. Halved square to have eastern and western portion, worked on eastern section to find the continuation of the wall. Moderate amount of pottery and flint found.  Had small to medium fieldstones, some ground stones. Came up on fill of wall and found southern line of wall. Separated 16/S/9 in south and 16/S/10 in north with 16/S/9 on the outside of the southern boundary of the wall.','1. layer  2. loose (extremely)  3. gray-brown  4. gravely/sandy-silty  5. small to fist-sized rocks (many)  6. 4m NS x 4m EW x 0.24 m deep  7. topsoil','Took 5 opening levels: 4 corners and center as instructed by Inbal.',NULL),(477,18,8,'F11','2016-06-05 00:00:00','2016-06-16 00:00:00','11.935','11.315','16/S/1, 16/S/2, 16/S/5',NULL,NULL,'Moving West from north face of W 003 into Philippe\'s old extension square, taking off rocks and tracing wall & surface. This material might be combined with 16/S/2 later. Combine pottery of 16/S/5 and 16/S/8 -- reconstructed pottery medieval.','1. layer  2. loose compact  3. brown  4. compact, moist  5. field stones  6. 58 cm EW x 2m NS x 31 cm deep',NULL,NULL),(478,18,9,'F12','2016-06-06 00:00:00','2016-06-19 00:00:00','12','11.8','16/S/7','16/S/16',NULL,'Southern portion outside of wall. More compact, less pottery, some fieldstones. Opened because it was south of large stones in a line (in line w/wall in F13) and appeared to have less rocks, but came up on more rocks and there did not seem to be any difference from the rest of 16/S/10. Later made to 16/S/16 when came across larger stones we could not take out. Accumulation or fill south of the remaining southern face of W 003.','1. layer  2. more compacted than 16/S/7  3. brown  4. clay  5. small to medium sized rocks (light compared to 16/S/10)  6. 2 m. E-W, .44 m. west side (running N-S), 1.0 m. east side (running N-S) x 20 cm. deep.',NULL,NULL),(479,18,10,'F12','2016-06-06 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','11.65','11.66','16/S/7','16/S/16, 16/S/14, 16/S/17',NULL,'NE part of square, opened because coming on more rocks and slight soil change, north of the wall. N of 16/S/9. Trying to define the core of the wall (before defining Wall 001). Began on East side of square as approximately 2 m. E-W x 2.6 m. N-S section, later opened up west side of square then closed 16/S/9 and made the entire 4 m. x 4 m. square 16/S/10, then opened up 16/S/14 (NW of square) and 16/S/16 (SE of square) so middle portion was still considered 16/S/10.','1. layer  2. compact  3. brown  4. clay, slightly silty  5. small-medium fieldstones  6. 4 m. N-S x 4 m. E-W.','16/S/17 was opened as a feature and then declared a wall (W 001), but sections not included in that have been considered 16/S/10 (NE and SW areas of square). This doesn\'t quite seem correct, but no work has been done in these areas recently. I believe this should have been done differently, but this follows Inbal\'s instruction.',NULL),(480,18,11,'F11','2016-06-06 00:00:00','2016-06-16 00:00:00','12.109',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'This locus is NW of the face of W 003. Removal of loose stones & dirt on top section to expose possible wall or surfaces. We moved mostly rocks and found more clearly W 004 running NS.','1. layer  2.  Loose soil  3. brown gray  4. --   5.  field stones and small boulders  6.  236cm N/S x 2m E/W x 25cm deep',NULL,NULL),(481,18,12,'F11','2016-06-07 00:00:00','2016-06-19 00:00:00','11.81',NULL,'16/S/11',NULL,NULL,'A probe in what might be an intersection of W 003 & W 004 to see if we can also see if W 004 was floating. This is a section closest to north face of W 003. The locus above is recorded in season 2015. Should partially equate with the top of 16/S/8. Includes foundation trench for W 004 that cannot be defined by soil but is defined by packed stones. Partially equated with 16/S/32, foundation trench E of W 004. Locus was expanded to find second course of W 004.','1. layer  2. moderately compact.  3. brown  4. moist, clay  5. pottery, basalt  6. 80cm NS x 1.32m EW',NULL,NULL),(482,18,13,'F11','2016-06-08 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','12.06','11.78',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Excavating western side of W 004 on north side of the 5x5 (excavated 2015). Finding west face of W 004. Only the top of the top course of the wall was defined here.','1. layer  2. loose  3. gray  4. silt  5.  pebbles, basalt, field stones  6. 40cm EW x 2m NS x 27cm deep',NULL,NULL),(483,18,14,'F12','2016-06-08 00:00:00','2016-06-09 00:00:00','11.60','11.384','16/S/10','16/S/20',NULL,'Rectangular/trench probe in NW corner of square to try and find face of a possible wall and determine if there are other information below small to medium fieldstones in square. Could be in a pit (lined by curve of large stones) or could be tumble of wall. Some stones (large) were flat lying and removed, could have been part of a wall or feature but unclear. Removed because -- this part of the square to determine what is going on underneath, and see if there is a second course of W 001.','1. layer  2.  slightly compact  3. brown-gray  4. clay  5. medium to large field stones  6. 1.4m N0-S x 1.7m E-W x 14cm deep 7. See a curved line of large stones on border.','Opened north of flat faced basalt stone suspected as part of northern face of W 001 in order to trace this wall eastward (continuation of W 003).',NULL),(484,18,15,'F11','2016-06-09 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','12.2',NULL,' ',' ',NULL,'Area of fill south west of wall 004.  Trying to find the southern face of wall 004. ','1. layer  2. loose  3. gray  4. silt, topsoil  5.  small pebbles,  field stones  6. 2m NS x 80cm EW ',' ',NULL),(485,18,16,'F12','2016-06-09 00:00:00','2016-06-09 00:00:00','11.986','11.83','16/S/9, 16/S/10','16/S/18',NULL,'Area south of line of stones that are part of the possible wall, 16/S/17. Encountered large stones, came up on compact brown soil with smaller stones. Was probably tumble.','1. layer  2. slightly compact  3. brown  4. clay  5. large, packed stones  6. 1.6m EW x 0.90m NS x 10 cm deep',NULL,NULL),(486,18,17,'F12','2016-06-09 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','12.17',NULL,'16/S/10','Wall 004',NULL,'CANCEL - defined as Wall 001','1. feature (or installation)  2. loose soil between many rocks   3. fill w/ gray brown soil  4. gravely  5. rocks, large, filled with small-medium stones 6. 2.3m W- N-S x 2.25m E - N-S x 4.17m E-W(ish)  7. possibly part of a wall, but designated as feature','Designated as a feature (Inbal\'s word) or installation (Ian\'s term) because believed to be something but Inbal did not yet wish to call it a wall.',NULL),(487,18,18,'F12','2016-06-09 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','11.88','11.73','16/S/16',NULL,NULL,'Less rocks, more compact, brown soil, south of probably wall (16/S/17). Some flat stones at the bottom.','1. layer  2. compact (more than 16/S/16).  3. brown soil  4. clay  5. small stones  6. 1.6m E-W x 0.9m N-S x (???) deep  7. brown soil has gray material mixed in which may be mudbrick debris.',NULL,NULL),(488,18,19,'F11','2016-06-09 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','12.2',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cleaning and articulation of top of W 004.','1. top of W 002 (W 004?)  2. loose   3. gray  4. silt  5. pebbles  6. 43cm EW x 2m N/S',NULL,NULL),(489,18,20,'F12','2016-06-09 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','11.46','11.36','16/S/14',NULL,NULL,'North-west corner north of W 001, inside curved procession of rocks that may [be] tumble from wall. Closed when encountered flat lying small stones (same level as pavement of 16/S/30).','1. layer  2. finer, medium compaction  3. reddish brown  4. clay-silt  5. fist-sized fieldstones  6. 1.4m N-S x 1.7 m E-W x 6 cm deep',NULL,NULL),(490,18,21,'E11','2016-06-14 00:00:00','2016-06-15 00:00:00','11.77','11.33','16/S/6','16/S/23',NULL,'Removing small stones to expose large stones that are part of a wall (most likely) closed to remove large stones in SE corner. Can see a line of rocks that are part of a wall in the west, while in the SE corner the rocks are tumble or part of a larger pi','1. layer  2.  loose  3. gray-brown  4. sandy-silty  5. small to large fieldstones  6. 4.1m N-S x 2.4 m E-W x 3 cm deep',NULL,NULL),(491,18,22,'E11/10','2016-06-14 00:00:00','2016-06-15 00:00:00','12','11.46','x','16/S/25',NULL,'Westward expansion of E11 to uncover wall. Topsoil, equivalent to 16/S/6 but expansion west. Expanded by 1 m. Topsoil down to rocks. Opened to see west face of the extension of W 004. Changed locus to begin removing some stones.  Equates with 16/S/6, L','1. layer  2.  loose  3. gray-brown  4. sandy-silty  5. small to medium fieldstones  6. 1m EW x 4.1m N-S x 13 cm deep 7. westward expansion',NULL,NULL),(492,18,23,'E11','2016-06-15 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','11.76','11.48','16/S/21',NULL,NULL,'East of continuation of W 004, removing rocks that appear to be part of rock tumble but may also have been part of a pit. Clearing to expose stones that may be part of something else. Large rocks were clearly tumble due to their angles/overlap.','1. layer (tumble)  2. loose  3. grey-brown  4. sandy-silty  5. medium to large fieldstones, snail shells  6. 1.25m EW x 1.8 m N-S x ??? Deep  7. removal of rocks',NULL,NULL),(493,18,24,'F11','2016-06-15 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','11.74','11.5','16/S/11','16/S/28',NULL,'Probable foundation trench for Wall 004 on eastern side of wall. Small to medium fieldstones, a few large fieldstones. Few to no rocks underneath. Small amount of pottery. The rocks were tightly packed, thought at first to be packing in the foundation','1. layer  2. compact  3. brown-dark gray  4. silty-clay  5. small to large fieldstones  6. 75cm EW x 1.1m N-W x 20 cm deep 7.',NULL,NULL),(494,18,25,'E11/10','2016-06-15 00:00:00',NULL,'11.87','11.37','16/S/22',NULL,NULL,'Removing stones from west of wall (continuation of W 004) that have no order and exposing the face of the W 004. Found stones (large) in a line on the south end of the locus that we kept in place. These appear to be a wall or extension off the wal','1. layer  2. loose  3. grey-brown  4. sandy-silty  5. small to medium fieldstones, some large stones, snail shells, tuft, mudbrick material  6. 4m NS x 0.55m WE x 31 cm deep  7. exposing face of wall 004',NULL,NULL),(495,18,26,'F11','2016-06-16 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','12.01',NULL,'(blank)',NULL,NULL,'Probe west of W 003 and east of W 004 where walls may abut. Investigated to determine if there was a disturbance from a pit or some other activity from the Crusade/Medieval period as well as determine relationship between the two walls.  Did find M','1. probe  2. compact  3. reddish brown  4. clay  5. small to medium field stones  6. 1m EW x 40 cm N-S x 64 cm deep 7. probe by Wall 0023 & Wall 004 where they abut',NULL,NULL),(496,18,27,'F11','2016-06-16 00:00:00','2016-06-20 00:00:00','11.71',NULL,'NA','NA',NULL,'Cleaning section under W 003 to make straight. Soil varied, mix of two different kinds; a loose gray sandy-silty and a reddish brown moderately compact clay-like soil. Done to see stratigraphy better.','1. cleaning edge of W 003  2. loose to moderately compact (varies)  3. gray to reddish brown (varies)  4. sandy to clay-like  5. small to medium fieldstones  6. 2.1m EW x ~5 cm NS x 32 cm deep 7. this was a cleaning under the W 003 (sectioning) with',NULL,NULL),(497,18,28,'F11','2016-06-17 00:00:00',NULL,'11.55',NULL,'16/S/24','16/S/29, 16/S/30',NULL,'Probably accumulation. Little pottery and some small stones, under foundation trench for W 004. Possible that the western part of the locus was part of the foundation trench for W 004. Came on stones on south side of locus so closed the 16/S/28.','1. layer  2. fairly compact  3. light brown-grey  4. silty clay  5. a few small stones (mostly soil)  7. some mudbrick debris',NULL,NULL),(498,18,29,'F11','2016-06-19 00:00:00',NULL,'11.44',NULL,'16/S/28','16/S/33',NULL,'Under northern side of 16/S/28, possibly equating with 16/S/28. Same matrix. This locus possibly cut into adjacent 16/S/30 = early pavement. It could have been robbed. Digging this area revealed a gravel & pot sherd surface that we then began to trace.','1. layer  2. fairly compact  3. brown-grey  4. sandy-silty  5. some small stones, mostly none  6. 1.1m NS x 0.75 m EW x 11 cm deep',NULL,NULL),(499,18,30,'F11','2016-06-19 00:00:00',NULL,'11.44',NULL,'16/S/28','16/S/31',NULL,'Feature of fist-sized stones arranged packed together and flat on top. Probably pavement that was cut by a foundation trench for W 004. About a 20 cm gap between the stones and the wall. Neatly packed small/medium stones = pavement.','1. feature  2. fairly compact  3. gray-brown, very light  4. sandy-silty  5. fist-sized stones  6. 0.45m NS x 0.6m EW x 8 cm deep  7. feature of stones that may have been pavement',NULL,NULL),(500,18,31,'F11','2016-06-19 00:00:00',NULL,'11.36',NULL,'16/S/30, 16/S/28','16/S/33',NULL,'Below pavement of 16/S/30 (stone pavement feature). EB pottery. Thin layer of soil, no finds.','1. layer  2. moderately compact  3. reddish brown  4. silty  5.  none  6. 60cm EW x 50cm NS x 6 cm deep',NULL,NULL),(501,18,32,'F11','2016-06-19 00:00:00',NULL,'11.46','11.35','16/S/28',NULL,NULL,'Part of foundation trench Wall 004 that cuts 16/S/30 (pavement feature). Cuts into 16/S/30 and 16/S/31. Composed of soil','1. layer  2. moderately compact  3. brown  4. silty clay  5. some small stones  6. 35cm NS x 20cm EW x 4-9cm deep',NULL,NULL),(502,18,33,'F11','2016-06-19 00:00:00',NULL,'11.3',NULL,'16/S/29, 16/S/34',NULL,NULL,'Surface below 16/S/29 made of gravel and pottery sherds, possibly foundation for pavement made by stones of 16/S/30. Extends to north (outside square) and possibly both east and south, under surfaces & loci.','1. feature (surface)  2. very compact  3. NA  4. NA  5. gravel & pottery sherds that make up a surfaces  6. 1m EW x 0.7m NS',NULL,NULL),(503,18,34,'F11','2016-06-20 00:00:00',NULL,'11.33',NULL,NULL,'16/S/33',NULL,'Layer covering the surface of 16/S/33 removed while trying to expose the surface (16/S/33). Probably accumulation. Few finds.','1. layer  2. medium compactification  3. grey brown  4. silty  5. none  6. 0.7m NS x 1m EW x 3 cm deep',NULL,NULL),(504,18,35,'F11','2016-06-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'11.26',NULL,'16/S/37',NULL,'Area where found medieval pottery & metal. Soil just above feature of 16/S/37 (medium stones). Medieval pottery & metal artifact were above the stones 5 – 10 cm. Could be accumulation. Was originally thought to be a disturbed area, and above feature some','1. layer  2. medium compactification  3. grey brown  4. sandy-silty  5. none  6. about 1.3m NS x 1.3m EW (slightly irregular on edges, but this is the main part)  7. just above feature 16/S/37',NULL,NULL),(505,18,36,'F11','2016-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,'11.40','11.23','16/S/26',NULL,NULL,'Area north of W 003, immediately east of W 004, south feature 16/S/33, west of 16/S/37. Includes mudbrick material tracing area to find either surface of 16/S/37 or 16/S/33. Composed of mudbrick material with brown soil underneath, some of which was mixed in','1. layer  2. very compact  3.  light gray and brown mix  4. silty, clay (mudbrick)  5. pebbles, (unclear) material  6. 1m NS x 95cm EW (south) / 1.2m EW (north) x 12 cm deep  7. mudbrick material','We were digging this area to see if any of the surfaces (16/S/33 or 16/S/34) continued, but found mudbrick material. Dug up mudbrick material and then closed locus. It is possible 16/S/12 and 16/S/8 were above this.',NULL),(506,18,37,'F11','2016-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,'11.44',NULL,'16/S/35','NA',NULL,'Stone pavement feature, possibly, or stone deposit of some sort. Small/medium stones packed together. May have been damaged. It seems there was a pit above this, as seen from the medieval pottery that was found in 16/S/35.','1. feature  2. very  3. NA  4. NA  5. small/medium stones  6. 1.2m NS x 1.15m EW  7. not dug',NULL,NULL),(507,18,38,'F11','2016-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,'11.29','11.19',NULL,NULL,NULL,'NE corner, under mudbrick material. Found medieval pottery. May be part of a pit. Mix of brown soil & mudbrick material. Had bone, no flint.','1. layer  2. loose  3. brown and mudbrick mix  4. clay/silty  5. none  6. 0.9m NS x 0.65m EW x 10 cm deep  7. animal burrows (disturbing area)','I believe 16/S/5 was above this.',NULL),(508,18,39,'F11','2016-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,'11.41','11.22',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Mudbrick material north of W 003 on east side of square. Digging this area to determine the extent of surface of 16/S/37 (small/medium stones) but noticed it was mudbrick material, probably a result of collapse/melt /accumulation from W 003. There','1. layer  2. very compact  3. gray; brown (mix)  4. clay, silty clay  5. gravel-size stones, worn out body sherds (pottery)  6. 0.65m EW x 0.75m NS (west side) / 1m NS (east side) x 19 cm deep  7. animal burrows','I believe 16/S/5 was above this.',NULL),(509,18,40,'E11','2016-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,'11.34','16/S/23','16/S/41',NULL,'Removing soil to expose east face of W 004. Removing large stones. Keeping barrier of rocks & soil to south of locus which borders F11 until end excavation of this area to prevent damage to gravel surface (bedding) of 16/S/33 in F11.','1. layer  2.  loose  3. dark brown  4. silty-clay  5. medium - large fieldstones  6. 1.35m EW x 3.20m NS x 24 cm deep',NULL,NULL),(510,18,41,'E11','2016-06-22 00:00:00',NULL,'11.543','11.32','16/S/40',NULL,NULL,'Removal of small to medium stones, & soil to expose east face of W 004. Found some ground stones. There was mudbrick material at the bottom of the locus. Level of Crusader pottery in SE corner of locus [at height] 11.40 m.','1. layer  2. not very  3. dark brown  4. clayey silt  5. small to medium stones, roots  6. 1.35m EW x 3.20 m NS  7. it\'s hot, especially in the sun.',NULL,NULL),(511,18,42,'F11','2016-06-22 00:00:00',NULL,'12.17','11.81',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cleaning top of W 003 and articulating stones of fill of wall. No pottery/finds.','1. layer  2. loose (very)  3. gray-brown  4. sandy-silty  5. fist-sized to medium stones  6. 2m EW x 1.5m NS x 17cm deep  7. cleaning top of W 003','Not sure',NULL),(512,18,43,'F11','2016-06-22 00:00:00',NULL,'11.4','11.21',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Possibly part of a pit. On north side of square, immediately west of 16/S/38. Had a high volume of bone, some pottery, but little flint. May have been part of pit that 16/S/38 may have been, thought(?) from the animal bone. Had some large stones and small gra','1. layer  2. loose  3. brown (soil between stones)  4. NA  5. bone, medium/small rocks, some large  6. 50cm EW x 90cm NS','I believe 16/S/5 was above this, but am unsure ( not here for that part of the excavation).',NULL),(514,18,101,'N10','2016-05-29 00:00:00','2016-05-31 00:00:00','16.44','15.779','+','16/S/105',NULL,'Surface cleaning','1. layer  2. loose  3.grey  4. silt  5. fieldstones  6. NS) 4 x EW) 4 x D)~ 0.059m',NULL,NULL),(515,18,102,'N8','2016-05-29 00:00:00','2016-06-01 00:00:00','16.972','16.241','+','16/S/118',NULL,'Topsoil clearing and weeding','1. layer (topsoil)  2. very loose  3. dark browning orange  4. silt  5. many pebbles, medium field stones and occasional large field stones  6. 4x4 meters x D) 0.18m  7. surface clearing',NULL,NULL),(516,18,103,'N7','2016-05-29 00:00:00','2016-05-30 00:00:00','17.125','16.715','+','16/S/110',NULL,'Surface clearing','1. top soil, surface cleaning (layer)  2. loose soil with loose field stones (loose - crumbly)  3. greyish-brown  4. silty-sand  5. small bits of mudbrick, shell, field stones  6. NS 4m x EW 4m x  D)0.08m  7. top soil/surface cleaning',NULL,NULL),(517,18,104,'P8','2016-05-29 00:00:00','2016-05-30 00:00:00','17.42','17.17','+','16/S/109, 16/S/108','112','Surface cleaning of stone pile','1. layer (cleaning)  2. loose field stones  3. grey  4. small to middle-sized field stones  5. N-S) 4.0m x E-W) 3.0m x D) 0.18m',NUL