ork revealed wall to have only one preserved course.','1. layer  2. compact  3. greyish brown  4. silt  5. small fieldstones; patches of mudbrick material  6. 0.7m x 0.8m',NULL,NULL),(612,18,308,'Trench 1','2016-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,'17.52','17.2','16/S/304','16/S/309',NULL,'Removal of next layer of soil in western part of the trench. Collected pottery, flint, worked stone artifacts, several bone fragments, and a few ground stone pieces.','1. layer  2. loose soil  3. yellow-brown  4. silt  5. small & medium fieldstones  6.f  2.0m x 3.6m',NULL,NULL),(613,18,309,'Trench 1','2016-06-21 00:00:00',NULL,'17.30','17.07','16/S/308',NULL,NULL,'Continued to reduce part of trench west of wall, which would help to determine if cluster of large fieldstones along northern baulk were floating. The large stone perhaps a “pillar stone” rests on a layer of smaller stones. This stone also has intention','1. layer  2. varied - loose and more compact patches  3. reddish brown patches (mudbrick?); yellow-brown  4. silt  5. small fieldstones 6. 2.0m x 3.6m',NULL,NULL),(616,20,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'18S surface finds with no assigned locus number',NULL,NULL,NULL),(617,20,1,'E9/F9','2018-05-27 00:00:00',NULL,'11.96','10.72',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Opened at topsoil to begin and give idea of relationship between area S and squares to the east. Leveling area N of trehcn dug and outside W17/001 many stones at the center. Some small stones from erosion removed but some larger were kept as they could be a remainder of a wall. Closed after removal of topsoil.','1. Topsoil  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. greyish brown  \r\n4.  loose  \r\n5. stones, winter wash\r\n6. 2.50m E-W x 9.00m N-S',NULL,NULL),(618,20,2,'F9','2018-05-27 00:00:00',NULL,'11.96','11.49','18/S/1',NULL,NULL,'Starting locus in area topsoil and winter wash intermixed w/ stones of small size. SE quadrant of square. Brown topsoil w/ many small rocks. Stones not particularly dense. Reddish greyish mudbrick material appearing in NW corner.','1. topsoil  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. dark brown  \r\n4. loose  \r\n5. field stones  \r\n6. 2.5m x 2.5m','Locus closed when brought to same level of loci excavated west of W17/001 last season. Still strewn w/small stones not a packed as 18/S/3.',NULL),(619,20,3,'E9/E10','2018-05-28 00:00:00',NULL,'11.79','11.09','18/S/1','18/S/5',NULL,'Opened N of 18/S/2 to see if the large stones arranged N-S are a feature. Many small stones appear w/ of NW of stones are are kept. Locus slopes down significantly westward.','1. topsoil/subsoil  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. dark brown  \r\n4. loose  \r\n5. small stones  \r\n6. 3.55m N-S x 2.5m E-W','Pebbles across most of its bottom they are sense but not packed together. NW corner of locus has fewer stones. Closed to excavate NW corner as 19/S/5. Bullet case found at 11.36 in half with less stones.',NULL),(620,20,4,'D10','2018-05-28 00:00:00',NULL,'11.94','11.27','17//??','18/S/8',NULL,'Between walls 16/004, 16/007, and 17/001.  Taking apart a collapse','1. collapse  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. dark brown  \r\n4. loose & sandy  \r\n5. stones of various sizes\r\n6. 3.26m EW x 4.20m NS',NULL,NULL),(621,20,5,'E9/F9','2018-05-28 00:00:00',NULL,'11.31','11.15','18/S/3','18/S/11',NULL,'This locus was opened as a small probe. NW corner below 18/S/3 excavated separately because of fewer stones. Brown reddish loose soil w/ less stones than 18/S/3 which is above. Closed to open 18/S/11 right below. Some small stones stick out from the surface. Below soil is more mudbrick.','1. mixed topsoil + some detrites  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. reddish brown  \r\n4. silt and clay  \r\n5. some small stones and detritus   \r\n6. 1.5m N-S x 1.4m E-W','Flint and bone may have gone uncollected due to lack of recognition by someone not an archaeologist.',NULL),(622,20,6,'?','2018-05-28 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(623,20,7,'E9','2018-05-28 00:00:00',NULL,'11.57','11.35',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Opened N of 18/S/3 in E part of N-S strip, 2.5m-wide, to level area to 2017 excavations (W 17/001). Soil not as packed as in loci S of this. Basalt bowl found. Possible NE-SW wall found w/one clear pace and two large stones could be another.','1. topsoil and slight subsoil  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. brown  \r\n4. silt w/ some clay  \r\n5. small and large stones\r\n6. 2.04m NS x 1.70m EW','Some finds tagged with square D9',NULL),(624,20,101,'N10','2018-05-27 00:00:00','2018-05-27 00:00:00','15.07','14.97','-','18/S/102, 18/S/103, 18/S/104, W001',NULL,'Cleaning, winter wash, few centimeters, south of wall from 2017. Came across Wall 001 very quickly so loci were changed.','1. Winter wash, layer\r\n2. moderately loose\r\n3. Brown/gray\r\n4. dirt/clay\r\n5. small pebbles, some pottery',NULL,NULL),(625,20,102,'N10','2018-05-27 00:00:00','2018-06-06 00:00:00','14.99','14.83','18/S/101, 18/S/104, 18/S/131','18/S/150, 18/S/153',NULL,'North of Wall 001 and south of wall from 2017, 18/S/104 (HB) was partially in this layer. Small pieces of charcoal-like material found while excavating PT003 and PT004. \nLikely to be foundation deposit.  Contains human remains in a secondary context','1. Layer  \r\n2. Compact  \r\n3. Brown  \r\n4. Mudbrick-like material  \r\n5. Pottery, small rocks','All sherds kept for EB',NULL),(626,20,103,'N10','2018-05-27 00:00:00','2018-06-18 00:00:00','15.04','14.62','18/S/101',NULL,NULL,'South side of wall 001, trench going down to try to find bedrock or other features','1. layer  \r\n2. compact  \r\n3. brown \r\n4. mudbrick-like material  \r\n5. pottery, small rocks','All PT sent to Restoration; locus is thought to be related to 18/S/156 and 18/S/171',NULL),(627,20,104,'N10','2018-05-27 00:00:00','2018-05-28 00:00:00','14.98','14.90',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Human bone, crushed, skull, in compact mudbrick material.  Level taken on top of skull before removal, and level taken under skull once it was removed. Cross-reference 17/S/284 PT002 LB003.','1. Human bone  \r\n2. crushed skull  \r\n3. gray  \r\n4.   \r\n5. teeth, bone \r\n6. spread over 1/3 square meter','No PT; LB only',NULL),(628,20,105,'N10','2018-05-27 00:00:00','2018-05-27 00:00:00','15.19','15.07','none','18/S/110',NULL,'Cleaning, winter wash, few centimeters, North of wall from 2017','1.  Winter wash, layer \r\n2. Moderately loose  \r\n3. Brown/gray  \r\n4. dirt/clay  \r\n5. small pebbles, some pottery',NULL,NULL),(629,20,106,'P6/P7','2018-05-27 00:00:00','2018-05-28 00:00:00',NULL,'16.60',NULL,'18/S/112, 18/S/113',NULL,'Cleaning first day',NULL,NULL,NULL),(630,20,107,'P6','2018-05-27 00:00:00','2018-05-29 00:00:00','16.64','14.66',NULL,'18/S/124, 18/S/125, 18/S/126',NULL,'First locus opened this season in P6. First layers of soil were cleaned and sections straightened. A good amount of flint blades was found.\nADDITIONAL INFO:  3 perforated objects found.  Large basalt socket (left from 2017 season) was finally removed','1. Cleaning locus  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. light brown  \r\n4. very large stones, small stones  \r\n5. bone, very large amount of flint and pottery  \r\n6. initially, the whole area of P6, then L111 was separated from it',NULL,NULL),(631,20,108,'P7','2018-05-27 00:00:00','2018-05-30 00:00:00','16.67','16.55',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cleaning of the whole square P7, excluding 18/S/106 and 18/S/109 which we suspected were pits. PT006 was opened in this locus on May 29 to bring down soil abutting large ground stone in the NW corner of square.','1. cleaning -- fill\r\n2. mix of different soils (includes clearing of fill of mudbrick & pit material)\r\n3. brown-grey\r\n4. silt to silty-clay\r\n5. range of stones (small, mid-size, large)\r\n6. 4m x 4m',NULL,NULL),(632,20,109,'P7','2018-05-27 00:00:00','2018-05-31 00:00:00','16.35','16.33','18/S/108','18/S/140',NULL,'Opened because we noticed a large group of stones, possibly an intrusive pit. This was closed when we removed all of the mid- to large-sized stones in the middle of the locus, better defining the exterior boundaries of \"pit 18/S/140\"','Removal of stone pile P7 (S)\r\n1. fill, possibly stone-lined pit\r\n2. loosely packed\r\n3. greyisy brown\r\n4. silt soil w/ some silty clay-like patches\r\n5. many mid-sized field stones, some larger stones\r\n6. ca. 1m (E-W) x 2m (N-S)',NULL,NULL),(633,20,110,'N10','2018-05-27 00:00:00','2018-05-30 00:00:00','15.18','14.93','18/S/105',NULL,NULL,'Taking down North of wall from 2017 to float the wall. Small amount of burnt mudbrick material around same level and areas as in 18/S/122.','1. layer  \r\n2. moderately compact  \r\n3. brown  \r\n4. clay/dirt  \r\n5. pottery, small rocks',NULL,NULL),(634,20,111,'P6','2018-05-28 00:00:00','2018-05-29 00:00:00','16.56','16.44',NULL,'18/S/127',NULL,'Area behind a semi-circular line of big stones. Residual of some form of tumble.\nADDITIONAL INFO: Locus opened behind a semi-circular line of studes, separating it from what appeared to be more loose material.  Mostly its S part was excavated','1. Pile of rock collapse (?)  \r\n2. Loose with occasional mudbrick  \r\n3. light brown  \r\n4. big and medium stones  \r\n5. flint, bone, 1 perforated stone object, groundstone',NULL,NULL),(635,20,112,'P6/P7','2018-05-28 00:00:00','2018-05-29 00:00:00','16.60','16.44','18/S/106','18/S/128',NULL,'Locus opened when 18/S/106 was level and the soil became a brown mudbrick-like material. We excavated ca. 15 cm on E side of the N-S running stones to float them. When we leveled 18/S/112 to the soil E of it, we closed 18/S/112 to remove the floating stones.','Mud brick matrix  \r\n1. layer  \r\n2. compact  \r\n3. brownish orange  \r\n4. mud-bricky matrix  \r\n5. a few pebbles to cobble-size stones  \r\n6. ca. 1m (E-W) x 1m (N-S)',NULL,NULL),(636,20,113,'P6/P7','2018-05-28 00:00:00','2018-05-28 00:00:00','16.85','16.49',NULL,'18/S/128',NULL,'This locus was open for the removal of a line of stones that were possible a late enclosure. Once the stones were found to be floating & higher up than the E-W stones bordering the N & S side of 18/S/112, we decided to remove the stones.','Removal of stones in \"stone lined pit\" \r\n1. wall removal  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. grey (stones)  \r\n4. mid-sized field stones  \r\n5. only stones  \r\n6. ca. 1m line of stones, N-S, single tier',NULL,NULL),(637,20,114,'P6/P7','2018-05-28 00:00:00','2018-05-30 00:00:00','16.77','16.35',NULL,'18/S/135',NULL,'Opened this locus to explore possible pit in a  stone-lined semicircular section overlying P6/P7 baulk into P7 on S half of square.  We closed this locus when better defined external parameters were clarified. As we suspected, the pottery is mixed!','1. Possible semi-circular stone line pit fill  \r\n2. Mixed matrix of loosely packed soil and mudbricky patches  \r\n3. brownish silt  \r\n5. lots of midsized cobble - field stone inclusions  \r\n6. ca. 1.8 m (N-S) x 2.0 m (E-W) x D 0.4 m  \r\nSee notes','Closed locus when came down on compacted mudbrick matrix',NULL),(638,20,8,'E10','2018-05-28 00:00:00',NULL,'11.37','11.21','18/S/4','18/S/13',NULL,'Opened below collapse in 18/S/4. Brown soil with small and medium sized stones. Closed when level of rest of area reached between walls 17/001, 16/007, and 17/001','1. layer  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. righ brown  \r\n4. siltt with some clay  \r\n5. small + medium sized stones  \r\n6. 1.70 NS x 1.80m EW',NULL,NULL),(639,20,9,'E/F 9/10','2018-05-29 00:00:00',NULL,'11.52','11.23',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Opened W of wall 17/001 and new expansion westward.  Area in front of blockage unexcavated for the moment,. To N it stops at large basalt stone.  Patch of small to medium stones. Soil is grey-reddish silty/dusty mudbrick material.','1.  layer  \r\n2. somewhat loose  \r\n3. reddish-grey  \r\n4. clay and silt  \r\n5. small and medium sized stones  \r\n6. 2.96m NS x 1.88m EW\r\n7. possibly worked bone and sea shells found',NULL,NULL),(640,20,10,'F9','2018-05-29 00:00:00',NULL,'11.70','11.29','18/S/2',NULL,NULL,'2.5 x 1m E-W trench below 18/S/2 in SW corner as probe.  Brown soil, many stones.','1. Probe  \r\n2. Somewhat compact  \r\n3. Brown  \r\n4. Clay with some silt  \r\n5. Medium & small stones\r\n6. 2.5 EW x 1m N-S',NULL,NULL),(641,20,115,'P6/P7','2018-05-28 00:00:00','2018-05-28 00:00:00','16.53','16.49','18/S/113','18/S/119, 18/S/128',NULL,'Locus opened to remove soil beneath the singe line of N-S stones of possible partition wall that was removed in 18/S/113. We closed this when the soil was level w/ 18/S/108 to the West.\nNo pottery or finds.','Soil under 18/S/113 (removal of stones in \"stone line pit\")\n1. layer (fill beneath wall)  \n3. light grey  \n4. silty  \n5. few small stones  \n6. ca. 1m (N-S) x 0.20 m (E-W)',NULL,NULL),(642,20,116,'P7','2018-05-28 00:00:00','2018-05-28 00:00:00','16.67','16.55','18/S/108','18/S/118',NULL,'Removal of stone feature in SE corner of square P7 -- planned & drawn last year. No finds or pot. Drawn in 2017 but not given wall number as unclear if architecture. Stones found to be floating so removed.','1.  Disassemble stones of \"wall\" in SE corner  \r\n2.  Stones -- loose, floating  \r\n5.  Large stones in no order, floating',NULL,NULL),(643,20,117,'N10','2018-05-29 00:00:00','2018-05-29 00:00:00','15.33','15.02','18/S/110','18/S/120',NULL,'Removal of 17/S/WL024\r\nDismantiling wall of one course','1. Wall  \r\n2. Compact  \r\n3. Light brown  \r\n4. Clay / mudbrick-like material\r\n5. large and medium stones, some pottery',NULL,NULL),(644,20,118,'P7','2018-05-29 00:00:00','2018-05-30 00:00:00','16.67','16.31','18/S/140, 18/S/108, 18/S/116','18/S/133',NULL,'Opened the locus originally to remove soil beneath small line of stones in SE corner of P7. It was realized that the whole of P7 running north to the P7/N7 baulk was the same layer, the debris above the mudbrick material to the north.','1. Fill beneath removal of 18/S/116 & higher soil north of removed wall and extensions N & W.\r\n2. loosely pack\r\n3. greyish-brown\r\n4. silty soil\r\n5. small-mid size stones\r\n6. 4 x 2 m (4m N-S x 2m E-W)',NULL,NULL),(645,20,119,'P6/P7','2018-05-29 00:00:00','2018-05-29 00:00:00','16.53','16.44','18/S/108, 18/S/115','18/S/128',NULL,'This locus was opened to level the fill beneath 18/S/113 & 18/S/115, and level the soil to the east and west. When 18/S/119 came down to a compact mudbricky matrix layer (18/S/128), the locus was closed.','1.  Fill beneath removal of layer 18/S/113  \r\n2. Loosly packed w/ some more compact patch  \r\n3. brownish-orange  \r\n4. silty clay  \r\n5. some small pebbles, rare cobbles\r\n6. ca. 1m (N-S) x ca. o.5m (E-W) x D ca. 10 cm',NULL,NULL),(646,20,120,'N10','2018-05-29 00:00:00','2018-05-29 00:00:00','15.23','15.00','18/S/117','18/S/121, 18/S/122, 18/S/123',NULL,'Beneath wall, 18/S/117 changed to new loci when burnt mudbrick material, oven material found at center of wall, and larger rocks were uncovered at south east end of wall.','1. Layer  \r\n2. Compact  \r\n3. Light brown  \r\n4. Mudbrick-like material  \r\n5. pottery, small rocks  \r\n6.',NULL,NULL),(647,20,121,'N10','2018-05-29 00:00:00','2018-05-30 00:00:00','15.19','14.93','18/S/120',NULL,NULL,'Rocky area under wall removal. Medium field stones, compact dirt, stone area under south east end of wall from 2017, ant nest.','1. layer  \r\n2. compact  \r\n3. brown  \r\n4. clay/compact dirt  \r\n5. medium stones',NULL,NULL),(648,20,122,'N10','2018-05-29 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(649,20,123,'N10','2018-05-29 00:00:00','2018-05-30 00:00:00','15.13','14.91','18/S/120',NULL,NULL,'Mudbrick type material, imbedded with many small fragments of pottery and rocks, below cut into wall.','Fill under wall removal.\r\n1. Layer  \r\n2. Compact  \r\n3. Brown / light brown  \r\n4. mudbrick-like material  \r\n5. pottery, small rocks',NULL,NULL),(650,20,124,'P6','2018-05-29 00:00:00',NULL,'14.76',NULL,'18/S/107',NULL,NULL,'Small corner within stones (WL003, WL004)\r\n2. loose, especially closer to a surface  \r\n3. greyish brown  \r\n4. medium stones  \r\n6.  Triangular.  \r\nNorth side: 50cm W-E  \r\nEast side: 70 cm N-S  \r\nWest side: 60 cm SE - NW','After the locus was opened in a small corner it was dug deeper and a mudbrick(?) surface was encountered',NULL,NULL),(651,20,125,'P6','2018-05-29 00:00:00','2018-05-30 00:00:00','14.66','16.25','18/S/107','18/S/139',NULL,'Locus was opened because medium/large stones were forming a semi-circle, suspected of being an installation. It was not. After removing the stones, the whole area was uniform and joined in 18/S/139.','Within semi-circle of stones\r\n1. layer  \r\n2. loose with many medium stones  \r\n3. light brown  \r\n4.  silty sand  \r\n5. medium stones',NULL,NULL),(652,20,126,'P6','2018-05-29 00:00:00','2018-05-30 00:00:00','see Notes','16.37','18/S/107',NULL,NULL,'Empty area within a later line of stones, in the S half of the square, excluding a semi-circular line of rocks (18/S/125) and small corner (18/S/124).','Empty area around 18/S/124 / 18/S/125\n1. layer  \n2. loose  \n3.  light brown  \n4. a lot of small stones  \n5. flint and bone  \n6. semi-circular, ca. 4m.','Lowest opening level 16.04?\r\nHighest closing level 16.37',NULL),(653,20,11,'E9/F9','2018-05-29 00:00:00',NULL,'11.16','10.96','18/S/5',NULL,NULL,'Continuation of excavations for 18/S/5.  Probe.  \nFar fewer stones than previous locus and the degraded bedrock beneath gives the soil a reddish color. Mixed highly degraded pottery found. On diagnostic sherd, a rim of an unidentified period/type.','1. layer  \r\n2. slightly compact  \r\n3. reddish brown  \r\n4. clay and silt  \r\n5. few small stones  \r\n6. 1.5m N-S x 1.4m E-W\r\n7. excavated to bedrock','Non-pottery finds may have gone unrecognized and not been collected',NULL),(654,20,12,'E9/E10','2018-05-29 00:00:00',NULL,'11.36','11.17',NULL,'18/S/24',NULL,'West of W17/001 and east of W18/011','1. layer\r\n2.  slightly compact  \r\n3. greyish brown  \r\n4. silt and clay  \r\n5.  few small-med stones, very few burnt mudbrick fragments\r\n6. 3.27mN-S x 2.50m E-W',NULL,NULL),(655,20,13,'E9','2018-05-31 00:00:00',NULL,'11.29','10.99','17/S/33, 18/S/8',NULL,NULL,'Below 17/S/33 extended to include area below 18/S/8.','1. layer  \n2. slightly compact  \n3. brown  \n4. mostly silty, some clay\n5. small-med. Stones\n6. 2.50m NS x 2.70m EW',NULL,NULL),(656,20,14,'F9','2018-05-30 00:00:00',NULL,'11.36','11.18','18/S/10',NULL,NULL,'Continuation of E-W trench. Below locus 18/S/10. Opened due to soil change. Red color appearing in soil suggested nearness to bedrock. Excavated down to bedrock.','1.  layer  \r\n2. slightly compact  \r\n3. reddish brown  \r\n4. silt and some clay  \r\n5. some small-med stones, very few small burnt mudbrick fragments  \r\n6.  1.20m NS x 3.60m EW',NULL,NULL),(657,20,15,NULL,'2018-06-04 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(658,20,16,'?','2018-05-30 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(659,20,17,'?','2018-05-30 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(660,20,18,NULL,'2018-05-30 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(661,20,19,NULL,'2018-05-31 00:00:00',NULL,'11.44','10.78',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Opened to find southern extent of wall 18/011. To find western and northern directions as well as to articulate the wall. Small and medium stones found to the west of the wall.','1.  area around Wall 18/011  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. dark brown  \r\n4.  \r\n5. small + medium stones\r\n6.',NULL,NULL),(662,20,20,NULL,'2018-05-31 00:00:00',NULL,'11.72','11.15',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Opened to clarify if line of stones is a wall or not. Northwest of wall 17/001 and east of locus 18/S/3.','1. layer\r\n2. loose soil, tightly packed rocks \r\n3. brown/grey  \r\n4. frequent large and small rocks  \r\n5. silt and clay\r\n6.   \r\n7.  very little pottery or worked basalt',NULL,NULL),(663,20,127,'P6','2018-05-29 00:00:00','2018-05-30 00:00:00','16.48','16.25','18/S/107, 18/S/111','18/S/136, 18/S/137, 18/S/138',NULL,'Locus was split into two loci after discovering a wall. This locus is North of WL002','Northern half of P6  \r\n2. loose, some mudbrick material  \r\n3. light brown  \r\n5. medium and large stones, bone, flint, pottery',NULL,NULL),(664,20,128,'P6/P7','2018-05-29 00:00:00',NULL,'16.48','16.44','18/S/108, 18/S/112, 18/S/119',NULL,NULL,'We opened this locus to excavate the space between two E-W running lines of stones. Soil was very compact w/ a color change from locus above. Cobbles are emerging in the SW corner of the locus. We noticed a stone installation w/ burnt material in the W section at the same height as rectilinear cobble-stone installation (also burnt) to the N under the mudbrick collapse in P7/N7.','Mudbrick matrix, fill beneath 18/S/108 / 18/S/112 / 18/S/119.  \n1. layer\n2. compact\n3. orangish-brown\n4. clay, mudbrick matrix\n6. 1.70m (E-W) x 1.00m (N-S)',NULL,NULL),(665,20,129,'P6','2018-05-30 00:00:00','2018-05-30 00:00:00','16.4','16.55','18/S/126','18/S/139',NULL,'Large empty area of rather loose soil. We just continued lowering it, changing loci to 18/S/139 and then 18/S/179.','SW half of the square  \r\n1. layer  \r\n2. rather loose  \r\n3. medium brown  \r\n4. silty sand  \r\n5. medium stones  \r\n6. 3m WE, 3m NS making[?] small triangle','Notice that levels are not consistent',NULL),(666,20,130,'N10','2018-05-30 00:00:00','2018-05-31 00:00:00','14.94','14.74','18/S/121, 18/S/122',NULL,NULL,'Medium and large stones under 18/S/121 and 18/S/122, possible collapse mess from wall 005','1. layer  \r\n2. moderately compact  \r\n3.  brown  \r\n4. dirt/clay  \r\n5. pottery, medium and large stones',NULL,NULL),(667,20,131,'N10','2018-05-30 00:00:00','2018-06-13 00:00:00','14.95','14.71','18/S/102, 18/S/110, 18/S/123',NULL,NULL,'Non-rocky area North of W 001, lots of small pottery and rocks lodged in slightly loose dirt, same as 18/S/143 in square M10.','1. layer  \r\n2. moderately loose  \r\n3. light brown  \r\n4. dirt/clay  \r\n5. pottry, small and medium rocks',NULL,NULL),(668,20,132,'N6/N7','2018-05-30 00:00:00','2018-06-18 00:00:00','16.58',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'topsoil','removal baulk',NULL,NULL),(669,20,133,'P7','2018-05-30 00:00:00','2018-06-14 00:00:00','16.43','15.95','18/S/118, 18/S/145','18/S/184, 18/S/196, 18/S/197',NULL,'Locus opened to excavate into debris sitting on burnt mudbrick already exposed last season. Opened PT007 for the first 5 cm. pass into the mudbrick. When Ian articulated burnt mudbrick, we opened PT009 to take another 5 cm. pass into the mudbrick East of the burned bricks. Locus began in P7 excavating mudbrick material. The mudbrick extended into N7. Now defined mudbrick have separate loci.','debris above mudbrick  \r\n1. layer  \r\n2. very compact  \r\n3. orange brown w/ patches of lighter whitish grey  \r\n4. clay /mudbrick / mudbrick debris \r\n5. clean mudbrick matrix  \r\n6. 4m (E-W) x 1.2m (N-S) x D 0.50m',NULL,NULL),(670,20,134,'N7','2018-05-30 00:00:00',NULL,'16.20',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Disassembling stones in N7 from previous season. We opened this locus to remove stones in square N7. We are trying to understand if the stones are later disturbance or possibly some being part of the original \"destruction horizon.\"','1. Layer  \r\n2. loose, stone  \r\n3. grey & brown  \r\n4. silt & stones  \r\n5. mainly stones  \r\n6. 2m (N-S) x 1.5m (E-W)','Called P6/P7 on some tags',NULL),(671,20,135,'P6/P7','2018-05-31 00:00:00','2018-06-07 00:00:00','16.53','16.10','18/S/114',NULL,NULL,'Excavated to remove possible fill from a pit. Came down on a mudbrick layer, likely the same as appearing in the surrounding loci to the N and E. I think this layer of mudbrick collapse is  part of a P7/P6-wide collapse that has since been robbed and disturbed by later activities in various loci.','Fill of pit w/ patches of mudbrick   \r\n1. layer (possible fill of pit?)  \r\n2. mix of loose & compact mudbrick patches  \r\n3. loose grey to compact brown patches  \r\n4. silty-clay  \r\n5. large and mid-sized stones  \r\n6. ca,. 2.5m (N-S) x 2.5m (E-W) x D 0.43m',NULL,NULL),(672,20,136,'P6','2018-05-30 00:00:00','2018-06-13 00:00:00','16.27','15.97','18/S/127',NULL,NULL,'Possible pit','SW side of 18/W002  \r\n1. pit?  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. darkish brown  \r\n4. silty sand  \r\n5. fallen mudbrick, small and medium stones\r\n6. trapezoid w/ approx. dimensions 1m on North, 1.5m on East, 1.5m on South',NULL,NULL),(673,20,137,'P6','2018-05-30 00:00:00','2018-06-13 00:00:00','16.38','16.16','18/S/127','18/S/185',NULL,'Small corner on the S side of 18/WL002 with a possible pit W of it. There are 3 stones in a line sticking out and as they were lying on more stones a new locus was opened (18/S/185) to expose them.','SE side of 18/W002  \r\n1. layer?\r\n2. loose  \r\n3. dark brown  \r\n4. silty sand  \r\n5. big stones  \r\n6. trapeziod  1m x 1m','From the Sketch Plan:  stones [in 18/S/137] form what appears to be a wall.  For this reason, 18/S/185 was opened.',NULL),(674,20,138,'P6','2018-05-30 00:00:00','2018-06-04 00:00:00','16.33','16.28','18/S/127','18/S/146',NULL,'Coming down on a possible surface. Removal of soil to articulate the stones of the northern part of the 18/W002','Northern area behind 18/W002.  \r\n2. mixed  \r\n3. medium brown  \r\n5. medium stones\r\n6. 340cm on N, 90cm on E, 300 cm on S','ADDITIONAL INFO:  Closed on 4 June was was worked only on 30 May.  After reaching the beaten surface it was left for a few days, closed, and a new locus, 18/S/146 was open in its place',NULL),(675,20,21,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(676,20,22,NULL,'2018-05-31 00:00:00',NULL,'11.51','11.16',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Excavating south of L012 and north of L009 to clarify the relationship between the two loci.','6.  0.60m NS x 2.00m EW\r\n7. Artificial/arbitrary baulk left by previous excavation.  Maybe suspected to be a wall in 2017?',NULL,NULL),(677,20,23,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(678,20,24,NULL,'2018-05-31 00:00:00',NULL,'11.24','11.07','18/S/12',NULL,NULL,'Opened to excavate a possible surface beneath locus 18/S/12.','1. layer  \r\n2. compact  \r\n3. grey  \r\n4. clay and silt  \r\n5. very few small to medium stones  \r\n6. see sketch',NULL,NULL),(679,20,25,NULL,'2018-06-03 00:00:00',NULL,'11.30','11.15',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Opened east of west face of wall 17/001 to see if stone pavement continues','1. layer  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. brownish grey  \r\n4. silt w/ some clay  \r\n5. frequent small stones  \r\n6.',NULL,NULL),(680,20,26,NULL,'2018-06-03 00:00:00',NULL,'11.67','11.17',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Opened to articulate eastern face of wall 17/001 and the corner with wall 17/007','1. layer  \r\n2. tightly packed stones with some soil  \r\n3. brownish grey  \r\n4. mainly silt, some clay?\r\n5. very frequent small to medium stones\r\n6.',NULL,NULL),(681,20,139,'P6','2018-05-31 00:00:00','2018-06-13 00:00:00','16.3','16.27','18/S/129, 18/S/125','18/S/179',NULL,'Big, flat, uneventful area of soft soil which we just kept lowering.','Southern half of P6 - excluding 18/S/124  \n1. layer  \n2. loose  \n3. light brown  \n4. silty clay  \n5. 40% of small stones, with occasional medium stones\n6. WE 2.5m / NS 2m',NULL,NULL),(682,20,140,'P7','2018-05-31 00:00:00',NULL,'16.33','16.07','18/S/109',NULL,NULL,'Locus opened to excavate fill in a pit in the SE corner of P7. The pit was identified when its loosely packed soil & rock inclusions distinguished it from the more compact mudbrick layer it cut into. We first traced the N & E edges of the pit, noting a difference in compaction although a change in soil color. Some mudbrick material was packed into the pit fill, as well as several very large stones. In order to find the southern boundary, we opened 18/S/149 to its south.','Removal of pit, southeast corner of square  \r\n1. fill\r\n2. very loosely packed, outer lining a more compact soil \r\n3. grey  \r\n4. silt, loose  \r\n5. many mid, large stones  \r\n6. ca 1m circular diameter',NULL,NULL),(683,20,141,'N10','2018-05-31 00:00:00','2018-06-13 00:00:00','14.87','14.64','18/S/130',NULL,NULL,'Pit/disturbance that cuts slightly into inside of wall 005 on north side, rocky disturbance','1. pit/disturbance  \r\n2. slightly compact  \r\n3. light brown  \r\n4. dirt/clay  \r\n5. small and medium stones, pottery, flint, bone \r\n6.',NULL,NULL),(684,20,142,'N10','2018-05-31 00:00:00','2018-06-18 00:00:00','14.84','14.55','18/S/131',NULL,NULL,'Small area of mudbrick material North of wall 005, inside of wall next to disturbance, floated wall.','1. layer  \r\n2. compact  \r\n3. brown  \r\n4. mudbrick-like material  \r\n5. pottery, small rocks, flint',NULL,NULL),(685,20,143,'M10','2018-06-03 00:00:00','2018-06-13 00:00:00','15.51','14.65','+',NULL,NULL,'Pit/fill, similar to 18/S/110 and 18/S/131, lots of small and medium rocks in moderately loose dirt.','1. possible pit  \r\n2. moderately loose  \r\n3. light brown  \r\n4. dirt/clay  \r\n5. small rocks, pottery, bone, flint',NULL,NULL),(686,20,144,'N6','2018-06-03 00:00:00','2018-06-11 00:00:00','16.14','15.95',NULL,'18/S/166',NULL,'Opened to continue work from the previous season to clear the stones and even out the surface.','Cleaning and removing stones in the NW corner of N6  \r\n1. layer  \r\n2. loose  \r\n3. light brown  \r\n4. silty sand  \r\n5. small and medium stones  \r\n6. 2m x 2m',NULL,NULL),(687,20,145,'P7','2018-06-03 00:00:00',NULL,'16.41','16.12','18/S/118',NULL,NULL,'Opened locus to peel off loosely packed grey soil & stones above mudbrick of 18/S/133. It appears to extend entire E-W of P7, continuing S toward a suspected pit in 18/S/140. Left an artificial section unexcavated ca. 30 cm between this locus & 18/S/140. Found sling stone; a team member said she might have chucked 1 or 2 others, not realizing their significance. We opened PT004 to remove baulk between 18/S/145 and 18/S/140 / 18/S/149 to the South.','1. layer  \r\n2. loose, rocky  \r\n3. grey  \r\n4. silt  \r\n5. many mid-small stones\r\n6.  ca. 3.5m (E-W) x 1.5m (N-S)',NULL,NULL),(688,20,146,'P6','2018-06-04 00:00:00',NULL,'16.28',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Possible surface which was sectioned and the W part excavated, then E part. Separate PT buckets 002 and 004 were made for removal of stones on the NW corner of the area. After going down ca 5 cm a darker, possibly burnt material was revealed','Possibe surface\r\n1. layer  \r\n2. compact, beaten surface?\r\n3. light brown, darkish brown  \r\n4. silty sand\r\n5. few medium stones, frags burnt mudbrick\r\n7. signs of burning?','Some finds tagged P6/N6',NULL),(689,20,147,'N6','2018-06-04 00:00:00','2018-06-11 00:00:00','16.14','15.89',NULL,'18/S/166',NULL,'Cleaning and lowering the SE part of N6.','1. layer  \r\n2. loose, compact in the S part  \r\n3. medium brown  \r\n4. silty sand  \r\n5. medium and small stones  \r\n6. 2.5m x 2.5m',NULL,NULL),(690,20,148,'M11','2018-06-04 00:00:00','2018-06-13 00:00:00','15.14','14.79','+',NULL,NULL,'Rocky area south of wall from last year.  Cut rocky area in half to see if there was anything different underneath,but still more stones','1. layer  \r\n2. slightly compact  \r\n3. brown  \r\n4. sirt/clay with large stones  \r\n5. large and medium stones, pottery, flint, bone, 1 small piece of oven material',NULL,NULL),(691,20,149,'P6/P7','2018-06-04 00:00:00',NULL,'16.31','16.23','18/S/108, 18/S/109',NULL,'18/S/145?, 18/S/140','Opened locus to explore southern boundary of the pit excavated in 18/S/140. 18/S/149 was opened as West half to catch the edge. Pretty quickly we came down on the mudbrick layer that seems to be appearing everywhere in the area, e.g. beneath 18/S/145 to the north, in 18/S/135 to the west, in 18/S/128, etc.','Section of pit 18/S/140 to South\n1. fill of pit  \n2. loose  \n3. grey  \n4. loose silt  \n5. mid to large-sized field stones\n6. ca 2m (E-W) x 2m (N-S)',NULL,NULL),(692,20,150,'N10','2018-06-05 00:00:00','2018-06-11 00:00:00','14.91','14.74','18/S/102','18/S/171',NULL,'Mudbrick-like material in Northwest corner, possible truncation of wall 001','1. layer  \r\n2. compact  \r\n3. light brown  \r\n4. mudbrick-like material  \r\n5. pottery, small rocks',NULL,NULL),(693,20,27,NULL,'2018-06-03 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(694,20,28,NULL,'2018-06-04 00:00:00',NULL,'11.36','10.97','18/S/24, 18/S/22, 18/S/9',NULL,NULL,'Excavating mudbrick material between walls W 17/001, W 18/011, and W 18/012','1. layer  \r\n2. compact  \r\n3. grey  \r\n4. silt and clay  \r\n5. few small to med stones','Read with locus 18/S/35',NULL),(695,20,29,'E11','2018-06-04 00:00:00',NULL,'11.53','10.99',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Excavating small E-W baulk obscuring the connection between W 16/004 and the Byz(?) wall.  Locus extended to include the \"platform\" left by previous excavation in this area.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(696,20,30,NULL,'2018-06-04 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(697,20,31,NULL,'2018-06-04 00:00:00',NULL,'11.61','11.33','18/S/3','18/S/34',NULL,'Removal of small and medium stones with some greyish brown soil to reach the mudbrick material found in 18/S/9.','1. layer  \r\n2. loose soil  \r\n3. greyish brown  \r\n4. silt and clay  \r\n5. small to med. Stones  \r\n6.  \r\n7. dense concentration of stones throughout locus',NULL,NULL),(698,20,32,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(699,20,33,NULL,'2018-06-05 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(700,20,34,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(701,20,35,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Read with locus 18/S/28',NULL),(702,20,151,'M6/N6','2018-06-05 00:00:00','2018-06-06 00:00:00','16.53','16.18','X','18/S/154',NULL,'Baulk removal (M/N6) topsoil  \r\n1. layer \r\n2. loose an crumbly  \r\n3. grey, light brown  \r\n4. dry silty sand  \r\n5. large stones, medium stones  \r\n6. 4m x 0.5m','Topsoilof a baulk removal between M6 and M6','E corner removed as part of 18/S/155',NULL),(703,20,152,'N6','2018-06-06 00:00:00','2018-06-11 00:00:00','16.08?','15.95',NULL,'18/S/166',NULL,'The surface rocks w